1
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:19,000
BROKEN EMBRACES

2
00:01:42,458 --> 00:01:49,417
(Newspaper sheets)

3
00:01:55,708 --> 00:01:57,750
What's your name?

4
00:01:58,208 --> 00:02:00,125
"Harry Caine"

5
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:03,875
(Voiceover)" I used to be called Mateo
and I was a cinema director.

6
00:02:04,875 --> 00:02:09,833
From very young I was tempted about the idea
of being someone else, appart from myself.

7
00:02:10,375 --> 00:02:16,500
Living only one life was not enough,
so I invented a pseudonym, Harry Caine.

8
00:02:17,458 --> 00:02:21,583
An adventurer that, because of the destiny,
would become a writer.

9
00:02:22,583 --> 00:02:27,000
As of now, I made him sign all the scripts
and stories that I wrote.

10
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:34,292
For years, Mateo Blanco and Harry Caine
shared the same person, I,

11
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:41,083
but there was a moment in which,
abruptly, I could only be Harry Caine.

12
00:02:41,542 --> 00:02:47,833
I became my pseudonym,
a writer made himself, by himself.

13
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:55,667
There was only a detail that I hadn't forseen,
Harry Caine would be a blind writer."

14
00:02:57,583 --> 00:02:59,708
Oh dear... Ernesto Martel has died!

15
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:01,083
Who?

16
00:03:01,542 --> 00:03:05,125
Ernesto Martel.
I know a granddaughter of his...

17
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:07,333
So he's dead...

18
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:08,958
Yes. Did you knew him?

19
00:03:09,208 --> 00:03:10,958
No...

20
00:03:13,208 --> 00:03:19,042
Let's see... What does interest you?
Politics, economics, culture...?

21
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:21,167
You interest me.

22
00:03:21,625 --> 00:03:26,083
How are you?
Do you mind describing yourself?

23
00:03:30,292 --> 00:03:31,792
What are you interested on?

24
00:03:32,792 --> 00:03:35,042
Your measures, for example?

25
00:03:35,583 --> 00:03:38,583
Em... 90, 68, 90 (cms).

26
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:42,417
What is the colour of your eyes?

27
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:47,333
Green, and in summer a bit blue.

28
00:03:47,875 --> 00:03:51,917
And your hair?
How are you dressed?

29
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:59,208
I'm blond, with long and straight hair.

30
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:05,667
I'm wering a purple t-shirt,
tight jeans...

31
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:08,792
Tight?

32
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:11,792
Yes, tight.

33
00:04:12,042 --> 00:04:13,167
And high heels.

34
00:04:13,417 --> 00:04:14,625
High?

35
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:16,917
Very high.

36
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:27,750
Let's see..., blond, long hair.

37
00:04:28,917 --> 00:04:36,167
Let's see... the eyes, green eyes...
a bit blue in the summer

38
00:04:36,417 --> 00:04:44,292
And the skin... Mmmm, delicious skin!
And the lips...

39
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:50,333
fleshy...

40
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:15,333
(pleasure grunts)

41
00:05:41,125 --> 00:05:42,750
May I go to the toilet?

42
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:47,000
(Breatheless) Yes, yes, of course!
At the end of the corridor.

43
00:05:49,667 --> 00:05:53,792
(Doorbell)

44
00:05:59,042 --> 00:06:01,708
(Keys)

45
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:05,250
Sorry, I thought you were alone.

46
00:06:05,708 --> 00:06:07,125
May I come in, or you are going for a second one?

47
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:10,333
No, no, come in.
We have finished.

48
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:17,125
She helped me to cross the road...
and I invited her to read me the newspaper...

49
00:06:17,375 --> 00:06:22,000
Of course...
She gave you the hand and you took the arm!

50
00:06:24,542 --> 00:06:25,708
What are you looking for?

51
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:27,667
My polo.

52
00:06:28,042 --> 00:06:30,375
There you go, the polo.

53
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:31,750
Thanks.

54
00:06:31,917 --> 00:06:34,250
Anything else? The socks?

55
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,375
Yes, thanks.

56
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:38,667
There you go.

57
00:06:38,792 --> 00:06:40,042
Thanks.

58
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:42,958
(WC flushing)

59
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,333
(Surprised) Hello...

60
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:52,833
(Unfriendly) Hi.

61
00:06:54,875 --> 00:06:58,583
Well then, Harry,
I'll be going.

62
00:06:59,042 --> 00:07:00,583
Thanks for crossing me.

63
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:01,875
No problem.

64
00:07:02,042 --> 00:07:03,167
You're standing on my feet.

65
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:05,792
Oops, Soory! sorry...

66
00:07:06,292 --> 00:07:07,833
No, it has been a pleasure.

67
00:07:08,042 --> 00:07:09,625
Same.

68
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,208
Thank you very much.

69
00:07:13,083 --> 00:07:15,250
So..., I have to go.

70
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:17,458
I hope we will meet again.

71
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:19,417
Yes...

72
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:30,958
Harry, you can't bring home the first
person that helps you cross the road!

73
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:32,625
One day something will happen!

74
00:07:32,875 --> 00:07:38,875
Everything that has to happen to me has already
Happened. Now I only have to enjoy life.

75
00:07:41,625 --> 00:07:45,042
Diego told me that you and him finished
the script yesterday.

76
00:07:45,792 --> 00:07:48,375
I'd like to add a final epilogue.

77
00:07:48,625 --> 00:07:52,333
I had agreed to bring the final version
to the producer and the director today.

78
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:55,125
You will have it tomorrow, have no fear

79
00:07:56,417 --> 00:07:59,625
Ernesto Martel has died.

80
00:08:03,208 --> 00:08:05,542
I think he was very sick...

81
00:08:05,792 --> 00:08:09,208
We haven't spoken about him for a long time...

82
00:08:11,125 --> 00:08:12,750
Yes, is true.

83
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,083
(doorbell and keys)
Hello.

84
00:08:17,458 --> 00:08:19,042
You look terrible!

85
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:20,458
I came running.

86
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:26,167
Today is Monday. Don't run for me, Diego.
We are not in a rush.

87
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:29,208
I am, I had made an arrangement.

88
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:33,208
You will have it tonight, don't worry.
Diego, shall we correct the ending?

89
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:34,875
Now?

90
00:08:35,292 --> 00:08:36,792
Yes.

91
00:08:37,667 --> 00:08:39,625
Start thinking on the next script.

92
00:08:39,875 --> 00:08:45,042
Something with fantasy or terror for kiddies,
is what it sells best.

93
00:08:45,292 --> 00:08:47,417
I'm not sure if I'll know...

94
00:08:48,708 --> 00:08:54,292
I thought of following the story
inspired in Arthur Miller's son.

95
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:56,167
The writer who married Marilyn?

96
00:08:56,458 --> 00:08:57,667
Yes.

97
00:08:57,833 --> 00:09:01,167
He was in "Vanity Fair",
I've read it in "El País" (spanish newspaper).

98
00:09:01,417 --> 00:09:06,583
After Marilyn, he married the photojournalist
Inge Morat and they had a son.

99
00:09:06,958 --> 00:09:11,292
The kid was born with Down Syndrome
and Arthur Miller hid it.

100
00:09:11,625 --> 00:09:15,958
He doesn't even mention him in his memories
and never wanted to see him.

101
00:09:16,625 --> 00:09:20,333
Despite his wife begging,
he never wanted to see him.

102
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:23,583
How terrible!

103
00:09:24,042 --> 00:09:27,000
But one day they met by chance.

104
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:30,958
Arthur Miller was giving a conference
in defense of a mentally handicapped person

105
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:35,458
who had been sentenced to death
after a forced confession.

106
00:09:35,917 --> 00:09:39,000
Amidst the public there was his son
with Down Syndrome.

107
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:44,083
After the conference, the son went to the
stand and hugged effusively his father.

108
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:47,958
Arthur Miller had no idea how to
shake that man off,

109
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:51,292
until the unknown man released him
and told him:

110
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:57,542
"I'm your son Daniel
and I'm very proud of you, dad".

111
00:09:59,875 --> 00:10:04,625
I don't think we can write about Arthur
Miller without asking for the rights to the family.

112
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:10,125
About the guy, the thing is not the meanness, but the strenght

113
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:14,500
that survives without the slight resentment
against the father that has ignored him for life.

114
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:21,708
No, no, yes... the topic is really interesting...
But years ago, when you started writing again...

115
00:10:22,042 --> 00:10:28,167
and I to sell your scripts, you said you wouldn't
write remakes, sequels or biopics.

116
00:10:28,417 --> 00:10:31,167
(Nervous) I remember perfectly,
because I was surprised about the biopics.

117
00:10:31,625 --> 00:10:35,125
But this wouldn't be a biopic, but a story
of superation and natural goodness.

118
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:37,292
(Doorbell)

119
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:39,292
Yes, no, of course. I'll go and open.

120
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:46,000
Hey, I've bought yogurts, but you're still
missing cleaning stuff and juices, that you have none.

121
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:48,292
And remember, the clothes from the laundry.

122
00:10:49,917 --> 00:10:51,750
Hey, guys, I'm off!

123
00:10:52,167 --> 00:10:53,375
OK, OK, fine.

124
00:10:53,542 --> 00:10:54,875
We'll talk about it, Harry.

125
00:10:55,083 --> 00:10:57,083
Ok, Judith, Ok..

126
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:07,042
(Song: "Vitamin C" By "CAN"
"Communism, Anarchism & Nihilism")

127
00:11:16,167 --> 00:11:18,500
Hey!
How are you?

128
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:21,958
Fine, and you? Fine.
Did you bring me something by the "Presets"?

129
00:11:22,208 --> 00:11:25,708
Very hot, just brought here by "the donkey" (emule).
Beautiful.

130
00:11:27,958 --> 00:11:31,625
Hey, do you want a bit of "crystal"? (type of methamphetamine)

131
00:11:32,417 --> 00:11:37,583
Nah. I need to sleep from time to time.
Then vouch for me.

132
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:42,167
Be more discreet.
But if we're almost alone!

133
00:11:47,417 --> 00:11:52,667
Hey, invite me to a drink, no?
Ask whatever you want.

134
00:11:53,125 --> 00:11:55,917
Do you want anything?
No.

135
00:11:58,333 --> 00:11:59,750
Sorry!

136
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,417
(Computer Voice) "Applications,
explore, Internet, properties, press arrow

137
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:06,417
up, arrow down, escape, error,
email, quit,

138
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:13,875
configure applications, explore internet,
the page has zero links, Obituary...

139
00:12:14,083 --> 00:12:22,500
The businessman Ernesto Martel has died. Obituary.
The businessman of chilene origin Ernesto Martel

140
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:25,083
died yesterday in his residence
in La Moraleja, Madrid.

141
00:12:25,458 --> 00:12:29,583
Living in Spain since kid, Martel was one
of the top businessman of the 90's.

142
00:12:29,917 --> 00:12:33,750
"Ermar Capital", empire created at the end
of the 80's, was key in the finantiation

143
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,958
of important public infrastructures
in Latin countries.

144
00:12:37,208 --> 00:12:41,125
Married twice and father of two, his
public figure started to diffuminate recently

145
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:44,250
when he was involved in the financial scandal
of the "Apresto Case".

146
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:48,625
Accused of fraud and tax evasion,
in 2002 he was charged with 3 years in prison,

147
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,292
of which he only served four months
because his age and disease..."

148
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:57,167
Yes... I've just spoken with the Ministry of
Transport and everything is on the move now...

149
00:12:57,417 --> 00:13:02,875
Yes, we're going to do the metro of Caracas...
Of course, of course, there's a lot of money...

150
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:07,167
Well, at least five years.

151
00:13:08,542 --> 00:13:14,333
Listen, I'm looking for a qualified company
and I'd thought of you...

152
00:13:14,792 --> 00:13:21,750
Sure. Everything will go through me,
the President himself has told me.

153
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:27,458
(Hears his mother calling)

154
00:13:32,625 --> 00:13:35,083
I'll call you later, ok?
I'll call you now.

155
00:13:35,542 --> 00:13:36,667
(internal line)

156
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:38,417
Yes, mister Martel.

157
00:13:38,542 --> 00:13:43,833
Lena, would you mind coming to my office?
I'm going to dictate a letter.

158
00:13:44,583 --> 00:13:46,750
Yes, I'm on my way.

159
00:14:01,083 --> 00:14:02,583
Hi, Lena.

160
00:14:02,792 --> 00:14:04,042
Good morning.

161
00:14:04,208 --> 00:14:06,125
The letter is for the Ministrer of Industry.

162
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,417
Right...

163
00:14:07,583 --> 00:14:10,042
Dear Antonio: I have the pleasure...

164
00:14:10,458 --> 00:14:12,375
Excuse me, sorry...

165
00:14:12,625 --> 00:14:13,792
Are you feeling all right?

166
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:14,875
Yes, yes.

167
00:14:15,042 --> 00:14:20,500
I have the pleasure of telling you that shortly
I will receive a comission from Venezuela...

168
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:24,167
Sorry.

169
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:29,042
Why don't you tell me what's happening?
I'm sure I can help you.

170
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:34,792
My father is very sick. He's being discharged
today and I'd like to go and pick him up in the hospital.

171
00:14:34,917 --> 00:14:37,083
Of course.
What does he have?

172
00:14:38,667 --> 00:14:41,833
He has a cancer in the stomach,
with metastasis.

173
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:44,958
Oh, I'm sorry.

174
00:14:46,042 --> 00:14:47,875
Thank you.

175
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:02,958
Where's dad?

176
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:04,958
He's inside, waiting.

177
00:15:05,208 --> 00:15:07,750
I can't believe
that they have kicked you out, like that

178
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,042
that they have let you out
like dogs.

179
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:12,625
Wasn't he going to be operated this week
by Dr. Álvarez de la Torre?

180
00:15:13,208 --> 00:15:14,708
Of course, that is what it was supposed to be!

181
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:18,375
He arranged a meeting this morning to
tell us that he was being discharged.

182
00:15:18,708 --> 00:15:20,250
I asked him what he meant.

183
00:15:20,583 --> 00:15:23,375
He says: "Ah, very easy.
It's july and I'm off on holidays".

184
00:15:23,625 --> 00:15:25,125
What do you mean on holidays?

185
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:26,583
I said: "Are we being kicked out?".

186
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:31,583
And he said: "No, madam, I'm discharging him
so he can go home".

187
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:36,167
"But, as he is how, what do I do with him at
home? He said: "That is a problem of yours".

188
00:15:36,417 --> 00:15:40,333
He added: "I'm off on holidays".
He is dying! I told him.

189
00:15:40,708 --> 00:15:44,083
"Then let him die relaxedly
in his home", he answered.

190
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:48,667
But you can't have him being tortured for 20 days
with the tests to operate him and leave him like that...

191
00:15:48,917 --> 00:15:53,042
(Whispers) Girls, have you forgotten about me?

192
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:54,875
Don't say such rot, dad!

193
00:15:55,083 --> 00:15:56,958
Nobody could ever forget about you!

194
00:15:58,208 --> 00:15:59,833
Let's do it slowly.

195
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:02,167
What a pleasure to go out, isn't it?

196
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:04,833
Let's go home...

197
00:16:14,667 --> 00:16:17,417
Come on, I'll put the bags in.

198
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:46,917
(Whispers) You are at home. What a pleasure...

199
00:16:47,167 --> 00:16:49,833
I'll bring you the "Sosegón".
Yes.

200
00:16:50,083 --> 00:16:52,000
Rest...

201
00:16:56,958 --> 00:16:59,292
Mum, I'm going. I've got to do plenty
of stuff... Ok?

202
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:00,667
Ok, darling.

203
00:17:00,792 --> 00:17:04,708
If anything happens, you call me, anytime.
I'll come tomorrow morning, ok?

204
00:17:05,083 --> 00:17:06,583
Thank you.

205
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:09,083
It's ok, mum.

206
00:17:10,708 --> 00:17:12,333
Be careful.

207
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,875
żMadame Milene?
Hi, it's Severine.

208
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:37,958
Severine! How long!
I'm glad to hear you.

209
00:17:38,208 --> 00:17:39,458
I need money.

210
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:40,750
When?

211
00:17:40,917 --> 00:17:44,083
Well, now! I've got the weekend off.
On weekdays I'm very busy.

212
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:46,500
I'll see what I can do for you, darling.

213
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:50,458
Can I call you tonight if I
find something?

214
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:54,000
Yes, yes, of course.
I await your call.

215
00:17:57,458 --> 00:17:59,875
(Phone)

216
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,708
Yes?

217
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:06,208
Severine?

218
00:18:06,458 --> 00:18:07,583
Who is this?

219
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:10,250
I'm phoning on behalf of Madame Milene.

220
00:18:10,792 --> 00:18:13,792
(they recognize their voices) You have the wrong number,
sir. Here doesn't live any Severine.

221
00:18:14,042 --> 00:18:17,000
I must have dialled the wrong number.
Sorry.

222
00:18:23,417 --> 00:18:25,875
The slices, madame.
Thank you, Alex.

223
00:18:26,208 --> 00:18:28,250
(Phone)
Hi. Has he called you yet?

224
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,708
(off) Who?

225
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:31,167
The customer! Who is it going to be?

226
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:33,458
But... How dare you to give my
number away?

227
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:34,958
I couldn't reject.

228
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:37,542
Things can't be done this way!
Are you mad or what?

229
00:18:38,292 --> 00:18:42,625
He knows everything about you. And I haven't told him a thing,
he found out on his own.

230
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:48,250
He knows you did your attempts as actress
and that some times... you have acted for me...

231
00:18:48,708 --> 00:18:52,833
Months ago he make me promise that, if you were to get
in touch with me again, I'd call him.

232
00:18:53,083 --> 00:18:55,042
I couldn't refuse, he is my best customer.

233
00:18:55,167 --> 00:18:56,833
(Hangs)

234
00:18:58,917 --> 00:19:05,667
(Phone)

235
00:19:07,292 --> 00:19:08,750
Yes?

236
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,792
Magdalena, daughter!

237
00:19:10,958 --> 00:19:12,750
Mum! How is dad?

238
00:19:12,958 --> 00:19:18,167
Very bad. We've had a terrible night
He hasn't stopped vomiting.

239
00:19:18,417 --> 00:19:24,417
He's vomiting blood, and everything...
As if it had exploded on the inside... I don't know what to do

240
00:19:24,667 --> 00:19:26,083
I'm on my way.

241
00:19:29,042 --> 00:19:34,208
(Phone)

242
00:19:39,042 --> 00:19:40,875
Yes?

243
00:19:41,125 --> 00:19:43,667
Mister Martel?
It's Lena.

244
00:19:43,917 --> 00:19:45,250
Good day... Lena.

245
00:19:45,583 --> 00:19:47,125
Good day.
I'm sorry to bother you...

246
00:19:47,458 --> 00:19:48,583
You never bother me.

247
00:19:48,917 --> 00:19:52,417
Look, I'm calling you because my
dad is dying.

248
00:19:52,667 --> 00:19:56,000
We must take him somewhere,
but I don't know where.

249
00:19:56,250 --> 00:20:01,042
He was discharged yesterday from the Manzanares Hospital
and we don't know what to do with him.

250
00:20:01,292 --> 00:20:08,292
Don't worry. We will take him into Emergency
in a private clinic. I'll take care of everything.

251
00:20:08,542 --> 00:20:12,542
Relax, madam. Doctor Blasco is the best
reagrding digestive in Europe.

252
00:20:12,792 --> 00:20:14,083
Here he is...

253
00:20:17,167 --> 00:20:18,667
How's the patient?

254
00:20:18,917 --> 00:20:22,000
You brought him in the worst conditions...
I assume you know already.

255
00:20:22,250 --> 00:20:25,542
Will you be able to save him?
I'm... Ernesto Martel.

256
00:20:25,792 --> 00:20:28,667
We will try our best, mister Martel,
but at the moment we can't operate him.

257
00:20:28,917 --> 00:20:30,542
And tomorrow?

258
00:20:30,792 --> 00:20:31,917
Tomorrow, maybe.

259
00:20:32,083 --> 00:20:36,292
We are feeding him via parenteral,
he will need some blood to recover.

260
00:20:36,542 --> 00:20:38,583
Do all you can to save him, doctor.

261
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:44,000
Don't doubt it. It's my obligation. I will inform you
about the evolution in the following hours.

262
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:45,750
Can I stay, doctor?

263
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:49,292
(Surprised) Yes, of course... You can stay with
him in his room for as long as you want.

264
00:20:49,667 --> 00:20:50,750
Thank you very much.

265
00:20:51,042 --> 00:20:52,708
I'll see you later.

266
00:20:53,417 --> 00:20:56,083
I don't know how to thank you for
everything you are doing for us.

267
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,458
I'm here for whatever you need, madame.

268
00:20:59,042 --> 00:21:01,708
Mum, Do you want me to stay with you?

269
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:04,292
No, go, darling.
You've done enough.

270
00:21:05,375 --> 00:21:06,708
Shall I bring you something to eat?

271
00:21:07,042 --> 00:21:10,958
Yes... no, leave it,
I'll manage myself, now.

272
00:21:11,208 --> 00:21:12,833
I'll call you later.

273
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:18,958
(Whispers) Thanks...

274
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:36,292
(doorbell)

275
00:21:54,542 --> 00:21:55,917
Who is it?

276
00:21:56,125 --> 00:21:57,333
It's Ray X.

277
00:21:57,500 --> 00:22:00,000
Ray X?
Nobody is named like that.

278
00:22:00,167 --> 00:22:04,042
It's a nickname.
In our age we took a lot of extasis.

279
00:22:04,208 --> 00:22:05,583
What do you want?

280
00:22:05,792 --> 00:22:08,792
I'd like to write a script with you,
for me to direct it.

281
00:22:09,042 --> 00:22:10,250
Are you a director?

282
00:22:10,417 --> 00:22:15,833
I did a very good documentary 14 years ago.
This would be my first fiction movie.

283
00:22:16,042 --> 00:22:18,917
Call Judith Garcia, my agent,
and explain her everything.

284
00:22:19,083 --> 00:22:21,917
If she finds it convenient,
she will arrange a meeting.

285
00:22:22,292 --> 00:22:26,292
And now I'd like to have a shower,
because you have caught me in the bathroom.

286
00:22:31,875 --> 00:22:34,333
Hey, are you going to stay there all day long?

287
00:22:34,542 --> 00:22:36,500
Well, you haven't given me Judith García's
phone number.

288
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:39,833
You figure it out. She's a well known
production director.

289
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,292
Am I going?

290
00:22:41,458 --> 00:22:43,625
(Off) Yes, go, go.

291
00:22:54,583 --> 00:23:00,042
(mobile phone)

292
00:23:00,417 --> 00:23:01,792
Yes?

293
00:23:01,917 --> 00:23:03,333
Hi, Harry. It is I.

294
00:23:03,542 --> 00:23:04,625
Hi, Judit.

295
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:09,583
I've received a phone call from a young director. His
name is Ray X and he wants to write a script with you.

296
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:10,875
Does it ring any bells?

297
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,042
Yes.

298
00:23:12,125 --> 00:23:15,042
He wants to see you this afternon,
or tomorrow, if you can.

299
00:23:15,250 --> 00:23:17,958
I've asked him an advancement, and he has agreed,

300
00:23:18,208 --> 00:23:21,292
but I won't be able to come because
I'm very busy with the Americans.

301
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:24,958
Well, I'll speak with him
and I'll tell you later.

302
00:23:25,167 --> 00:23:27,792
I hope you like him, he looks
like he could bleed money.

303
00:23:27,917 --> 00:23:29,125
Have you seen him?

304
00:23:29,250 --> 00:23:32,958
No, because of his voice. And because of the cheque
I'm going to ask him as soon as I hang up.

305
00:23:33,542 --> 00:23:37,542
I'll send Diego so you are not alone.
Kisses. Ciao.

306
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:44,458
Well, żAlicante or Barcelona?

307
00:23:44,625 --> 00:23:45,792
Barcelona.

308
00:23:45,917 --> 00:23:50,667
The director really wants Barcelona.
I think Alicante it's a better option.

309
00:23:57,792 --> 00:24:02,125
(Doorbell)

310
00:24:03,167 --> 00:24:04,542
Hello.

311
00:24:04,792 --> 00:24:08,375
I've got a meeting with Mr. Harry.
Yes, he's in his office.

312
00:24:22,333 --> 00:24:25,792
Hello, it's Ray X.

313
00:24:25,917 --> 00:24:30,167
How are you?
Sit down...

314
00:24:42,083 --> 00:24:43,792
Well, you tell me.

315
00:24:44,042 --> 00:24:48,500
I like your work a lot,
I've known it since the beggining.

316
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:55,250
Thank you. If you don't mind, let's get to the point.
What sort of story would you like to write?

317
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:57,958
(doorbell)

318
00:24:58,250 --> 00:24:59,292
Well...

319
00:24:59,417 --> 00:25:00,500
Yes?

320
00:25:00,958 --> 00:25:07,417
I'd like to write a story about the vengeance
of a son against the memory of his father.

321
00:25:07,708 --> 00:25:10,500
Why does the son want vengeance?

322
00:25:12,417 --> 00:25:15,083
Because the father nullified and
ruined his life.

323
00:25:15,333 --> 00:25:17,042
How?

324
00:25:17,625 --> 00:25:23,083
The father is a violent man, homophobic,
with no scruples and very powerful.

325
00:25:23,333 --> 00:25:29,250
The son, is a sensitive boy, with artistic
interests, but with complexes and weak.

326
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:32,042
He tries to please his father in everything.

327
00:25:32,292 --> 00:25:38,000
Despite being homosexual, he marries twice,
like him, and like him he also divorces, too.

328
00:25:38,333 --> 00:25:42,583
He has a son that hates him as much
as he hates his own father.

329
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:47,583
When the father dies,
the son can finally remake his life.

330
00:25:47,750 --> 00:25:53,000
This is his salvation, his revenge,
and the story I want to tell.

331
00:25:53,250 --> 00:25:56,000
Yeah... I'm afraid I'm not the
writer you're looking for.

332
00:25:56,167 --> 00:26:02,333
You are... You don't know to what extent.
I'll pay you as much as you want.

333
00:26:02,667 --> 00:26:04,750
It's too personal.

334
00:26:04,917 --> 00:26:06,625
Bring it to your ground.

335
00:26:06,875 --> 00:26:10,708
Thanks, but no. And now, if you don't mind...
Diego!

336
00:26:14,917 --> 00:26:17,375
I will leave my phone number.

337
00:26:17,667 --> 00:26:19,333
Please...

338
00:26:21,792 --> 00:26:23,417
If you change your mind...

339
00:26:23,750 --> 00:26:26,333
Please.
Let me alone!

340
00:26:28,083 --> 00:26:29,958
I'm sure we will see each other again.

341
00:26:30,167 --> 00:26:32,000
In my case, that would be a miracle.

342
00:26:32,125 --> 00:26:33,292
Please, would you come with me...

343
00:26:33,458 --> 00:26:34,667
I'm on my way!

344
00:26:35,750 --> 00:26:37,792
Good bye.

345
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:44,625
(leaves and closes the door)

346
00:26:46,875 --> 00:26:49,750
Son of a bitch!

347
00:26:51,917 --> 00:26:53,333
Don't you think he was talking about himself?

348
00:26:53,458 --> 00:26:54,917
I guess so...

349
00:26:55,083 --> 00:27:00,500
Look in the first drawer,
and search for the pictures of the filming of 94.

350
00:27:00,667 --> 00:27:03,167
Maybe he's in any...

351
00:27:24,958 --> 00:27:27,333
Keep looking.

352
00:27:43,417 --> 00:27:44,667
There he is!

353
00:27:45,125 --> 00:27:47,208
Describe me the picture.

354
00:27:47,458 --> 00:27:53,375
He's with you in the filming. He has long hair
and straight, and has a camcorder in his hand.

355
00:27:53,625 --> 00:27:54,958
I was almost sure.

356
00:27:55,167 --> 00:27:56,792
Who is he?

357
00:27:56,917 --> 00:28:01,292
Ernesto Martel's son.
What does he want?

358
00:28:03,292 --> 00:28:06,833
You can put the pictures back
in the drawer, and close it.

359
00:28:29,667 --> 00:28:33,167
(phone)

360
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:39,542
(Off Ex wife) "Hi Ernesto, it is I. I'm phoning you
because we must talk about our son".

361
00:28:39,792 --> 00:28:41,000
I can't talk now, Rosana.

362
00:28:41,250 --> 00:28:43,083
(Off) "I've caught him
wearing my dresses."

363
00:28:43,208 --> 00:28:46,500
It's your fault,
you've made him a wimp to humiliate me.

364
00:28:46,875 --> 00:28:49,417
(Off) "I'm going to send him to you.
In the end, it's your son."

365
00:28:49,667 --> 00:28:53,792
If I haven't been a good father in 19 years, I
don't think I'll learn to be a good one right now.

366
00:28:54,167 --> 00:29:00,792
I need to go. And tell Ernesto that if
he wants to speak with me, he has to call him. (hangs)

367
00:29:01,750 --> 00:29:03,583
Don't be so hard with them, Ernesto.

368
00:29:03,750 --> 00:29:05,042
Blackmailers!

369
00:29:05,167 --> 00:29:06,333
Come on, help me with the necklace.

370
00:29:06,458 --> 00:29:07,958
Yes, of course.

371
00:29:08,167 --> 00:29:10,042
Why don't you invite your son
to spend some days here?

372
00:29:10,208 --> 00:29:12,542
That's what his mother has just said.

373
00:29:13,208 --> 00:29:17,042
(whispers) But it would be better if
I didn't mix you with them, Lena.

374
00:29:17,292 --> 00:29:21,125
He will do me company.
Does he like either cinema or theatre?

375
00:29:21,292 --> 00:29:23,500
A lot, I think...

376
00:29:24,375 --> 00:29:27,125
The mother has told me that he's a bit gay.

377
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:32,875
If I invite him over I'd like you to tell me
if it's true, and if you think it can be fixed.

378
00:29:33,542 --> 00:29:34,958
And how am I going to know?

379
00:29:35,167 --> 00:29:36,208
I'm not asking you to fuck him...

380
00:29:36,375 --> 00:29:37,458
Well, thank you.

381
00:29:37,583 --> 00:29:39,750
But you notice about that sort of
things with the beautiful girls

382
00:29:39,917 --> 00:29:43,292
Look, call him, but don't
count on me for that.

383
00:29:44,125 --> 00:29:45,833
(Off)
"This is shameful, Ernesto!"

384
00:29:46,083 --> 00:29:48,750
"I'm not recriminating that we've divorced,
but that you are living with a man."

385
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,083
"What are your sons going to think!"

386
00:29:50,250 --> 00:29:55,000
That his dad is gay and that he has
very good taste, and a lot of luck.

387
00:29:55,500 --> 00:29:58,333
If they love me and you don't put them against me,
they will accept it.

388
00:29:58,583 --> 00:30:00,833
(Off) "You should have told me that
before we got married!"

389
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,333
If only you hadn't been so obsessed
with my father's money

390
00:30:03,583 --> 00:30:04,958
you would have noticed on your own
(phone)

391
00:30:05,083 --> 00:30:09,708
(Off) "What do you mean?"
I'll leave you, I have another call.

392
00:30:12,042 --> 00:30:15,667
I hope is not your other ex-wife.
I hope not!

393
00:30:16,333 --> 00:30:20,750
Don't ever marry, Mario.
No, as of now, it doesn't fit on my plans.

394
00:30:20,917 --> 00:30:21,958
(Off) Hello?

395
00:30:22,083 --> 00:30:23,375
It's Judit García.

396
00:30:23,500 --> 00:30:26,292
Ah, hi, Judit.
Did you get the money?

397
00:30:26,417 --> 00:30:31,042
I don't want it! I've just resent it to you.
Er-nes-to!

398
00:30:31,292 --> 00:30:34,417
Wasn't your name Ray?
That's my artistic nickname.

399
00:30:34,667 --> 00:30:38,042
Artistic?
What do you want?

400
00:30:38,292 --> 00:30:40,250
Erase my father's name.

401
00:30:40,417 --> 00:30:42,333
What's that got to do with Harry?

402
00:30:42,625 --> 00:30:44,708
I wanted to see him for a long time.

403
00:30:44,833 --> 00:30:48,167
And it's true that I want to film a movie
and I want him to write the script.

404
00:30:48,417 --> 00:30:50,958
I've got the lead actor...

405
00:30:52,458 --> 00:30:53,875
You are not a director!

406
00:30:54,042 --> 00:30:57,625
You should watch my documentary,
you would change your opinion.

407
00:30:57,833 --> 00:31:00,750
Ernesto, forget about us!

408
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:04,208
Don't be afraid of me.
I'm not my father.

409
00:31:04,458 --> 00:31:09,083
Don't get close to Harry. If you appear 'round
his house again, I'll denounce you for harassment!

410
00:31:12,042 --> 00:31:15,042
I don't fancy at all having to go searching for
location shoots outside Madrid,

411
00:31:15,375 --> 00:31:19,625
but the Americans are paying us a lot
and we need the money.

412
00:31:19,833 --> 00:31:22,542
Go relaxed.
Don't worry about me.

413
00:31:22,792 --> 00:31:29,417
Give me Tonino Guerra's book. I worry about
Harry, too. Take care of him whilst I'm away.

414
00:31:29,667 --> 00:31:32,833
I've got other things to do, mum.
I can't be all day long taking care of him.

415
00:31:33,083 --> 00:31:34,500
It's only two weeks!

416
00:31:34,708 --> 00:31:37,333
Harry can manage perfectly on his own.

417
00:31:37,500 --> 00:31:40,042
I'm worried about Ernesto JR.

418
00:31:40,167 --> 00:31:44,625
I'd like you to be around, to see if he comes
or phones, and that you tell me immediately.

419
00:31:44,875 --> 00:31:46,167
Why are you so worried?

420
00:31:46,417 --> 00:31:48,375
He's crazy.
I don't trust him.

421
00:31:48,625 --> 00:31:50,042
Why?

422
00:31:50,250 --> 00:31:51,458
It's a long story.

423
00:31:51,625 --> 00:31:52,833
Do a resume!

424
00:31:53,083 --> 00:31:55,958
Diego, please, it's not the time.

425
00:31:57,167 --> 00:31:59,208
It's never the time with you!

426
00:31:59,667 --> 00:32:03,583
If you are so concerned about taking care of Harry,
I'll quit my job and stay in Madrid!

427
00:32:03,750 --> 00:32:05,333
Or I could hire someone.

428
00:32:05,542 --> 00:32:10,250
No, mum, I'm not annoyed about going with Harry
but I'm fed up with so many secrets!

429
00:32:13,458 --> 00:32:15,417
When's your mother coming back?

430
00:32:15,583 --> 00:32:18,500
I didn't get it quite clear,
in around 10 days, I think...

431
00:32:23,292 --> 00:32:25,000
What are you looking at?

432
00:32:25,250 --> 00:32:26,792
A billboard that says "Give blood".

433
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,542
Do you want to give blood?

434
00:32:28,708 --> 00:32:32,000
No, no... I just thought that "Dona" (give, in spanish)
is a beautiful name for a woman.

435
00:32:32,333 --> 00:32:34,583
And "Dona Sangre" (give blood) is a good name for a movie.

436
00:32:34,833 --> 00:32:36,583
Yeah, it sounds allright.

437
00:32:36,875 --> 00:32:38,917
Sounds like a vampire movie.

438
00:32:39,125 --> 00:32:40,500
It's true.

439
00:32:40,750 --> 00:32:42,833
Imagine that after that ad
there's a group of vampires, waiting,

440
00:32:43,167 --> 00:32:45,750
working in hospitals and clinics
and that they keep the blood

441
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,167
they receive from the donors,
to get high afterwards.

442
00:32:49,417 --> 00:32:52,625
Your mother would like that story.
Let's write it.

443
00:32:53,708 --> 00:32:55,625
"Dona Sangre"("Give Blood")

444
00:32:56,083 --> 00:32:59,292
Vampires live like chinese people,
integrated in the spanish society,

445
00:32:59,542 --> 00:33:04,167
but without being noticed and, like the chinese,
they control various industries, too...

446
00:33:04,417 --> 00:33:06,375
Back sunglasses, for example.

447
00:33:06,500 --> 00:33:10,000
And night businesses:
Bars, discos, afterhours...

448
00:33:10,375 --> 00:33:14,083
As they don't need to be high to stay awake
they are the best workers for night shifts.

449
00:33:14,542 --> 00:33:16,375
And the industry of sun lotions!

450
00:33:16,625 --> 00:33:20,333
The vampires are worried about
the climate change, and the ozone layer.

451
00:33:20,583 --> 00:33:23,458
Their solar blocking creams are..
the best in the market!

452
00:33:23,708 --> 00:33:24,917
That is really good...

453
00:33:25,083 --> 00:33:29,708
It must be a very dense cream, like an armor,
so they are protected all day.

454
00:33:29,958 --> 00:33:34,292
The story would go like that...
a very beautiful woman, totally naked,

455
00:33:34,625 --> 00:33:37,208
applying her superdense cream
to her nice body,

456
00:33:37,458 --> 00:33:40,125
before going to work to the clinic.

457
00:33:40,375 --> 00:33:43,958
Her body ressembles white velved,
precious...

458
00:33:44,208 --> 00:33:48,125
What a good start!
We need a love story...

459
00:33:48,375 --> 00:33:53,042
A mixed love story,
between the young vampiress and a young mortal guy.

460
00:33:53,292 --> 00:33:57,708
She works in one of those clinics in which blood
donors go, and they get high with it.

461
00:33:57,958 --> 00:34:01,375
And the guy goes to donate blood to that clinic.
They fall in love very quickly.

462
00:34:01,917 --> 00:34:05,833
After the first needle goes in his vein,
she gets really randy.

463
00:34:06,083 --> 00:34:09,375
So, they start dating.
But she doesn't want to vampirize him...

464
00:34:09,625 --> 00:34:12,833
these vampires don't go against people
they don't bite humans.

465
00:34:13,083 --> 00:34:15,000
Unless it's absolutely necessary...

466
00:34:15,250 --> 00:34:17,292
But they like sex, don't they?

467
00:34:17,542 --> 00:34:22,292
Of course. That is going to be one of their problems,
because we need a bit of tension.

468
00:34:24,417 --> 00:34:28,958
The couple loves each other a lot, but when it's time
to fuck she slips away.

469
00:34:29,208 --> 00:34:30,333
But why?

470
00:34:30,583 --> 00:34:33,792
Because she's afraid of not being able to control herself
and bite your neck when she's in the process.

471
00:34:34,208 --> 00:34:36,333
When they're randy,
you can do anything to them.

472
00:34:36,542 --> 00:34:39,667
From the front, from behind...
Whatever you want, except kisses.

473
00:34:39,917 --> 00:34:41,542
And their breasts?

474
00:34:41,875 --> 00:34:44,333
Those are high risk practices.

475
00:34:44,583 --> 00:34:47,583
When he's with her breasts,
she has to cover her face with the pillow

476
00:34:47,917 --> 00:34:50,292
