00:53:00,333 --> 00:53:04,875
Yes, it's a non-stop.
It's a very absorbing job.

715
00:53:05,125 --> 00:53:07,167
Aren't you tired?

716
00:53:07,500 --> 00:53:13,083
Chocolate gives me energy. I love
bitter orange with chocolate!

717
00:53:13,875 --> 00:53:16,208
I meant the filming, not the chocolate...

718
00:53:16,583 --> 00:53:21,750
A lot. At the end of th week I'm very tired,
but I'm very happy.

719
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:24,125
I was thinking that we should
take a break.

720
00:53:24,375 --> 00:53:28,708
A weekend off, you and I, in
the house in Ibiza...no?

721
00:53:29,917 --> 00:53:32,458
We have rehearsals on the weekends.

722
00:53:32,833 --> 00:53:34,750
Don't you rehearse as well during the filming?

723
00:53:34,958 --> 00:53:36,125
Yes.

724
00:53:36,375 --> 00:53:38,833
What happens?
Do you spend the whole day rehearsing?

725
00:53:39,083 --> 00:53:40,792
Well, it's the way movies are made!

726
00:53:41,042 --> 00:53:44,542
How about the life of the rest? You
can't park it for months!

727
00:53:44,792 --> 00:53:47,792
Ernesto, the movie dictates.

728
00:53:48,042 --> 00:53:51,625
I'm sorry, I dictate...
I'm the producer.

729
00:53:53,708 --> 00:53:54,750
Any problems?

730
00:53:54,917 --> 00:53:57,625
Yes, we need some small atrezzo.
Everything is so impersonal!

731
00:53:57,875 --> 00:54:01,500
One thing is that I'm asking for a graphic decorator,
and the other is that it's completely dead!

732
00:54:01,750 --> 00:54:02,958
Should I speak to Antxon?

733
00:54:03,125 --> 00:54:05,333
No, no. I'll speak with him myself.

734
00:54:05,583 --> 00:54:08,458
What's wrong with you?
You have a bad face.

735
00:54:08,708 --> 00:54:14,917
Dieguito... I couldn't breathe for the whole night.
We haven't been able to sleep.

736
00:54:15,167 --> 00:54:17,000
Don't you know yet what is it?

737
00:54:17,250 --> 00:54:21,708
Some doctors say it's Asthma, others
that it's allgery, but we don't know what to.

738
00:54:22,167 --> 00:54:26,500
They keep investigationg,
but it's exhasperating.

739
00:54:26,750 --> 00:54:31,167
Well, take as as long as you need. Even if
we're filming, the important thing is your son.

740
00:54:31,417 --> 00:54:32,833
Thanks.

741
00:54:35,500 --> 00:54:38,250
One thing, I've been speaking to
the producer, too.

742
00:54:38,500 --> 00:54:39,708
And?

743
00:54:39,875 --> 00:54:43,375
He's complaining that the filming is
taking too much of Lena.

744
00:54:44,542 --> 00:54:47,125
So how does he think movies are made?

745
00:54:47,667 --> 00:54:50,542
Ernesto is a businessman,
not an artist.

746
00:54:50,792 --> 00:54:53,875
Well, maybe he shouldn't have gotten
into prouction. Nobody asked him.

747
00:54:54,042 --> 00:54:57,000
It's too late to discuss this now.

748
00:54:59,667 --> 00:55:04,500
This weekend he's off with her to Ibiza,
so you won't be able to rehearse.

749
00:55:05,500 --> 00:55:07,750
Son of a bitch!

750
00:55:08,625 --> 00:55:12,083
(Off Harry) "Well, let's see...
The laps out! The desk out!

751
00:55:12,208 --> 00:55:17,250
The chairs out! I've asked for
a graphic decorator, but one that is alive!

752
00:55:21,917 --> 00:55:30,958
(grunts and groans)

753
00:55:41,833 --> 00:55:44,583
(Deep breathe)

754
00:56:22,667 --> 00:56:28,667
(Deep breathe)

755
00:56:45,625 --> 00:56:52,125
(Groan)

756
00:56:58,333 --> 00:57:00,667
( )

757
00:57:09,750 --> 00:57:13,917
Oh dear! What a face,
my God!

758
00:57:57,000 --> 00:58:00,292
(SCREAM)

759
00:58:00,833 --> 00:58:06,333
Are you scared because I touch you...
but not scared because you see me dead?

760
00:58:06,875 --> 00:58:11,208
I didn't think you were dead.
I thought you were asleep.

761
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:14,125
I usually snore...

762
00:58:15,333 --> 00:58:19,667
If I thought you were dead, I wouldn't
have put the make up.

763
00:58:19,917 --> 00:58:24,667
Any man of my age could have a heart attack
after six fucks.

764
00:58:25,958 --> 00:58:29,333
You are not a man of your age...

765
00:58:33,042 --> 00:58:40,292
I wouldn't mind dying after fucking
with you days, weeks, months, years, centuries...

766
00:58:42,000 --> 00:58:47,875
I'm crazy for you, Lena.
You got me crazy, I think you know.

767
00:58:49,167 --> 00:58:52,792
Yes, I think I know...

768
00:58:53,042 --> 00:58:56,000
(Shouting) Action!

769
00:58:56,792 --> 00:59:00,083
Look what I found in the kerb,
they fell from your terrace

770
00:59:00,333 --> 00:59:02,667
(Serious, not acting)
They are presents from Mr. Iván and I threw them away.

771
00:59:02,917 --> 00:59:07,042
But you can't do this, Miss Pina.
You could kill someone...

772
00:59:07,292 --> 00:59:10,792
In Naples, on New Year's eve,
they throw even the furniture.

773
00:59:11,042 --> 00:59:14,250
My granny was napolitan
and I have got it in my blood.

774
00:59:14,500 --> 00:59:17,375
But this is not Naples, and
today isn't Christmas Eve.

775
00:59:18,750 --> 00:59:22,875
I was nervous, and it relaxes me to throw things...
You keep them.

776
00:59:23,125 --> 00:59:31,125
Ah, it's quite convenient...
"Love"...you say "Love", I say "Sexo".

777
00:59:31,375 --> 00:59:32,417
Cut!

778
00:59:32,667 --> 00:59:33,875
Should we check?

779
00:59:34,042 --> 00:59:35,792
What the fuck are we going to check!

780
00:59:35,958 --> 00:59:38,333
Come on, and I'll give you some touches afterwards, eh?

781
00:59:44,500 --> 00:59:46,833
You're in a very low tone, Magdalena.

782
00:59:47,042 --> 00:59:48,583
Yes, I know...

783
00:59:48,708 --> 00:59:50,167
What's wrong?

784
00:59:50,292 --> 00:59:52,583
(Crying) I'll tell you later

785
00:59:53,333 --> 00:59:54,542
Let's have a lunch break.

786
00:59:54,792 --> 00:59:55,875
30 minutes?

787
00:59:56,000 --> 00:59:56,833
Yes, yes, yes...

788
00:59:56,958 --> 00:59:58,625
Guys, 30 minute break for a
sandwich!

789
00:59:58,875 --> 01:00:03,417
Let's clear this a bit, and let's
go outside, please.

790
01:00:16,167 --> 01:00:18,417
(Off lip reader)
"No lips"

791
01:00:20,625 --> 01:00:23,625
"I've had a dreadful weekend".

792
01:00:23,875 --> 01:00:26,833
"We haven't rehearsed so
you could have a rest!"

793
01:00:27,083 --> 01:00:31,833
"Rest? I've had that son of a bitch
the 48 hours!"

794
01:00:32,208 --> 01:00:38,833
"He hasn't given me a second for a break,
the bastard. I'm on tranquilizers."

795
01:00:39,375 --> 01:00:41,000
"No lips"

796
01:00:43,875 --> 01:00:47,042
"No, no. I'll recover and do it."

797
01:00:47,292 --> 01:00:49,333
"Are you sure?"
"Of course"

798
01:00:49,583 --> 01:00:53,083
"You have to be sparking..., and light"

799
01:00:54,083 --> 01:00:58,500
"Of course... Light... Light!"

800
01:01:01,167 --> 01:01:08,083
You don't know what it is to have that
monster during 48 hours on you... Disgusting!

801
01:01:09,375 --> 01:01:14,542
"Better not to imagine it.
Better if you and I never speak of Ernesto."

802
01:01:14,792 --> 01:01:18,917
"That melon, better not to open it"

803
01:01:21,167 --> 01:01:23,875
What is he doing with his notebooks?

804
01:01:24,458 --> 01:01:26,000
I write on them until the end.

805
01:01:26,250 --> 01:01:27,542
And afterwards?

806
01:01:27,750 --> 01:01:28,833
I burn them.

807
01:01:28,958 --> 01:01:31,917
If you don't mind, I
prefer if the notebooks slept here.

808
01:01:32,083 --> 01:01:33,417
Notebooks sleep?

809
01:01:33,583 --> 01:01:37,458
Leave them here. You'll recover them tomorrow

810
01:01:37,708 --> 01:01:39,750
And when you've finished
I'll keep them.

811
01:01:40,000 --> 01:01:42,583
Very good. Whatever you say.

812
01:01:45,333 --> 01:01:46,708
At what time should I come tomorrow?

813
01:01:46,833 --> 01:01:49,125
They will call you once the material is ready.

814
01:01:49,708 --> 01:01:53,625
I assume that you are conscious
of the absolute confidenciality of your work.

815
01:01:53,875 --> 01:01:56,542
Of course.
Bye.

816
01:02:13,458 --> 01:02:14,917
Hi, Lena!

817
01:02:15,167 --> 01:02:16,792
Hello...

818
01:02:17,292 --> 01:02:21,417
My father asks me why I don't go to yoga
with you. I wonder the same.

819
01:02:21,667 --> 01:02:25,792
Well, you tell him that I'm grown up and free
and that I've forbidden you to follow me.

820
01:02:26,042 --> 01:02:27,583
You know I can't tell him that.

821
01:02:27,833 --> 01:02:29,833
Try it. It wouldn't hurt you.

822
01:02:30,042 --> 01:02:31,167
I can't.

823
01:02:31,375 --> 01:02:38,000
Look, do what you want, but you
are not coming with me, ok? Really, how annoying!

824
01:03:32,458 --> 01:03:34,625
Ernesto? What are you doing there!

825
01:03:35,083 --> 01:03:36,583
Working!

826
01:03:37,042 --> 01:03:40,667
Switch that off! Hasn't Mateo told you
not to film us outside the recording?

827
01:03:41,125 --> 01:03:44,708
My father has told me to ignore it.
He wants to see everything.

828
01:03:45,083 --> 01:03:48,458
You have no morals, none of you two!
Leave me alone for fuck's sake!

829
01:03:49,542 --> 01:03:51,917
I'm reminding you that I'm filming this.

830
01:03:52,250 --> 01:03:56,083
Stop, I'm telling you!
Stop it!

831
01:03:57,292 --> 01:03:59,417
I'm telling you to stop!
Give me the fucking camera!

832
01:03:59,667 --> 01:04:03,375
You are crazy! Let go!
You are crazy! My camera!

833
01:04:03,708 --> 01:04:06,375
Let it go for fuck's sake!

834
01:04:09,917 --> 01:04:12,375
( )

835
01:04:24,708 --> 01:04:26,542
(Door slamming)

836
01:04:26,833 --> 01:04:28,917
Focus on me.

837
01:04:36,625 --> 01:04:42,125
Ernesto, listen up.
Yes, I'm talking to you.

838
01:04:42,583 --> 01:04:47,958
I've just been with the man I love, and
I'm happier than what I've been in my whole life

839
01:04:49,208 --> 01:04:52,500
because that man also loves me....
a lot.

840
01:04:53,583 --> 01:04:57,167
Don't worry, because I'm going to leave you
relax, very soon.

841
01:04:57,417 --> 01:05:00,000
There is no need for you to spy on us.

842
01:05:01,167 --> 01:05:04,583
There's nothing to hide...

843
01:05:11,167 --> 01:05:14,167
(door slam)

844
01:05:30,958 --> 01:05:38,083
(steps getting closer)

845
01:05:42,417 --> 01:05:48,625
(steps walking away)

846
01:05:59,458 --> 01:06:04,917
(wood cracks)

847
01:06:13,417 --> 01:06:20,250
(ice clings)

848
01:06:28,625 --> 01:06:32,292
I don't know if today you arrived a bit
early or a bit late...

849
01:06:32,542 --> 01:06:34,167
It started to rain and we were unable to film.

850
01:06:34,417 --> 01:06:36,125
Where are you going?

851
01:06:37,333 --> 01:06:39,250
I'm leaving you, Ernesto.

852
01:06:39,417 --> 01:06:40,833
Shouldn't we talk about this before?

853
01:06:41,083 --> 01:06:42,917
I've already told you everything
I had to.

854
01:06:43,167 --> 01:06:46,250
Lena, please!
Please, Lena!

855
01:06:46,417 --> 01:06:47,458
Good bye...

856
01:06:47,625 --> 01:06:50,000
Lena, listen to me, Lena!

857
01:06:50,167 --> 01:06:51,917
Let me go!

858
01:07:16,042 --> 01:07:22,583
(grunts)

859
01:07:30,250 --> 01:07:35,083
Turn around, my love. I'll help you.
Let me do it.

860
01:07:36,292 --> 01:07:39,167
Don't worry, relax, I'll help you.

861
01:07:40,542 --> 01:07:44,667
You could have broken something.
I'll remove your shoes.

862
01:07:48,667 --> 01:07:51,250
You'll be more comfortable that way.

863
01:07:52,208 --> 01:07:58,542
I'll take care of everything. Cheer up.
Help me.

864
01:08:20,667 --> 01:08:24,167
My love, careful...

865
01:08:26,292 --> 01:08:32,083
Sit down, carefully... treasure.

866
01:08:32,333 --> 01:08:36,542
Like that... good...
I'll take you to hospital in a second.

867
01:09:11,708 --> 01:09:15,833
My wife fell down the stairs!
Very carefully, please.

868
01:09:16,083 --> 01:09:17,292
Let's see...

869
01:09:17,417 --> 01:09:19,250
Careful.

870
01:09:19,500 --> 01:09:21,542
The head...

871
01:09:22,833 --> 01:09:25,708
Relax, relax.

872
01:09:26,708 --> 01:09:29,167
Careful... Careful with the legs.

873
01:09:31,500 --> 01:09:33,750
We'll take her to trauma.

874
01:10:15,875 --> 01:10:17,375
May I use the phone?

875
01:10:17,625 --> 01:10:19,292
Not here, in the doctor's office.

876
01:10:19,458 --> 01:10:20,667
It's rather urgent.

877
01:10:20,833 --> 01:10:23,250
Don't worry.
We'll take her to the consultation room in a second.

878
01:10:25,167 --> 01:10:26,458
Mateo?

879
01:10:26,667 --> 01:10:29,792
Yes. What's the matter? Are you not coming?

880
01:10:30,042 --> 01:10:31,750
No, not tonight no.

881
01:10:32,000 --> 01:10:33,750
Is everything OK?

882
01:10:34,917 --> 01:10:39,458
There has been an accident.
But don't worry, everything is fine.

883
01:10:39,708 --> 01:10:42,708
We've got afternoon filming tomorrow.
Shal we see each other first before?

884
01:10:42,958 --> 01:10:48,125
No, I won't be able to. I've got plenty of stuff
to do. I'll see you directly in the sutiod.

885
01:10:48,375 --> 01:10:51,875
You sound weird, Magdalena.
Are you sure everything is all right?

886
01:10:52,000 --> 01:10:56,042
Yes. I'll see you tomorrow.

887
01:11:00,250 --> 01:11:03,542
(Off) Well, they're here.
Don't ask anything, ok?

888
01:11:11,708 --> 01:11:13,292
Are you OK, madam?

889
01:11:13,500 --> 01:11:14,542
I'm fine.

890
01:11:14,667 --> 01:11:15,792
Can I help you?

891
01:11:15,917 --> 01:11:17,125
It's not necesary, thanks.

892
01:11:17,292 --> 01:11:18,750
It hasn't been anything.

893
01:11:19,500 --> 01:11:23,333
Martin, please.
Open the door.

894
01:11:32,125 --> 01:11:35,417
Thanks for your discretion.

895
01:11:37,542 --> 01:11:41,333
Could you please remove your glasses?

896
01:11:50,333 --> 01:11:54,792
What do you want me to do?
What can I do for you to forgive me?

897
01:11:55,042 --> 01:11:56,542
Take me to the studio.

898
01:11:56,792 --> 01:11:57,917
You shouldn't move.

899
01:11:58,167 --> 01:12:00,708
If you don't take me, I'll go.
Even if I have to crawl.
Aunque sea a rastras.

900
01:12:00,958 --> 01:12:06,125
What are you going to say? How are
you going to explain the leg and the plaster and scratches?

901
01:12:06,375 --> 01:12:07,583
Depends on you.

902
01:12:07,833 --> 01:12:09,375
On me?

903
01:12:13,167 --> 01:12:17,708
I'll do whatever you ask me,
if you promise to stay with you.

904
01:12:20,250 --> 01:12:24,792
I will stay with you if you let
Mateo finish the filming,

905
01:12:25,042 --> 01:12:26,542
according to whatever he decides.

906
01:12:26,792 --> 01:12:29,875
He will start asking questions,
he's not an idiot.

907
01:12:30,125 --> 01:12:32,792
I'll say I tripped.

908
01:12:33,250 --> 01:12:35,500
How are you going to film, if you can't walk?

909
01:12:35,750 --> 01:12:40,417
He will decide that, but I want to make sure
that you will respect his decision,

910
01:12:40,667 --> 01:12:45,917
no matter the cost, or
the waiting time. Is that clear?

911
01:13:06,083 --> 01:13:08,625
I live there.

912
01:13:17,833 --> 01:13:22,167
And that's it. Ernesto is ready to
agree to whatever you decide.

913
01:13:22,417 --> 01:13:23,750
Decide, what?

914
01:13:23,958 --> 01:13:27,083
I can't go from a shot of you walking normal to
one in which you go in a plaster!

915
01:13:28,792 --> 01:13:31,250
How long do you have to wear the plaster?

916
01:13:31,500 --> 01:13:33,333
Three weeks.

917
01:13:33,667 --> 01:13:36,042
Do you mind if I speak a second with Lena
on our own?

918
01:13:53,792 --> 01:13:55,292
Tell me the truth!

919
01:13:56,500 --> 01:14:00,833
People don't fall off the stairs,
that only happens in the movies.

920
01:14:01,083 --> 01:14:02,792
(whispers) Be quiet, Mateo.

921
01:14:03,042 --> 01:14:06,958
We need to finish the filming as soon as
possible. Until then I won't be able to dump Ernesto.

922
01:14:07,208 --> 01:14:12,292
Why not? He's a psychopath!
What other proof do you need?

923
01:14:13,167 --> 01:14:15,083
My god!

924
01:14:25,458 --> 01:14:27,917
I can't go.
I've promised I'd stay with him

925
01:14:28,167 --> 01:14:33,125
in exchange that you finish the movie with
the conditions that you decide.

926
01:14:34,708 --> 01:14:37,167
No. There must be another solution.

927
01:14:37,417 --> 01:14:41,667
Which one? The only one is that I keep
living with him until you finish!

928
01:14:41,917 --> 01:14:43,833
What have you compromised to, exactly?

929
01:14:44,083 --> 01:14:48,542
To live under the same roof, he in his own bedroom, and
I in mine.

930
01:14:48,792 --> 01:14:50,083
He has no right to anything else.

931
01:14:50,333 --> 01:14:52,292
Do you think he's going to abide only to that?

932
01:14:53,167 --> 01:15:00,833
I don't know, but the sooner we finish
filming, the better. Make up something to avoid stopping!

933
01:15:04,000 --> 01:15:07,167
We only have got one stair scene

934
01:15:08,000 --> 01:15:11,125
We would have to repeat the ending...

935
01:15:11,792 --> 01:15:14,583
23 retake, one, first.

936
01:15:17,000 --> 01:15:18,833
(shouts) Action!

937
01:15:23,792 --> 01:15:26,125
So you are Ivan's ex wife?

938
01:15:26,375 --> 01:15:30,083
The one that has been in a physichiatric ward
for the last 20 years?

939
01:15:32,000 --> 01:15:35,000
Yes, but I'm not in any ward anymore.

940
01:15:35,333 --> 01:15:40,417
Now I'm here with you...
walking down the stairs...

941
01:15:40,667 --> 01:15:44,042
According to the note, it seems that
you are in a hurry to see him.

942
01:15:44,292 --> 01:15:45,708
Yes, but you walk first...

943
01:15:46,708 --> 01:15:51,875
No, the one in a hurry is you.
I've been waiting for 20 years.

944
01:15:52,333 --> 01:15:54,167
Come on...

945
01:16:04,417 --> 01:16:07,917
As I was telling you...
After breaking appart with my husband

946
01:16:08,167 --> 01:16:12,083
I went to the street and I found a
guy that was looking at me, very good looking.

947
01:16:12,750 --> 01:16:18,750
What an arse, feet... Well, I brought him
home and I fucked him several times.

948
01:16:19,000 --> 01:16:22,500
You know I'm very interested in sex
as a social matter.

949
01:16:22,833 --> 01:16:23,958
And how was it?

950
01:16:24,125 --> 01:16:28,000
In bed, godly, a virtuous.
Haven't seen anything like that.

951
01:16:28,167 --> 01:16:29,292
This is the good one.

952
01:16:29,417 --> 01:16:31,875
What a big toe!

953
01:16:33,375 --> 01:16:36,667
(Off Mateo) "Every morning,
Lena arrived destroyed to the filming.

954
01:16:37,125 --> 01:16:43,000
Based on repetition, there was always a shot
in which she overcame it and managed to do it good.

955
01:16:43,250 --> 01:16:46,667
The convivence with Martel
had become hell.

956
01:16:46,917 --> 01:16:49,458
Lena didn't tell me anything,
but it was obvious.

957
01:16:50,042 --> 01:16:55,917
When the filming had finished, I asked him to drop it,
but she was afraid for the movie.

958
01:16:56,167 --> 01:17:00,917
She didn't want to leave him, not until I had chosen
all the good shots.

959
01:17:01,167 --> 01:17:02,583
(Phone)

960
01:17:02,875 --> 01:17:03,917
(Off) Hello?

961
01:17:04,125 --> 01:17:05,667
(Off) It's Magdalena.

962
01:17:05,792 --> 01:17:07,083
(Off) Is everything ok, Magdalena?

963
01:17:07,333 --> 01:17:09,875
(Off) No. I'm down here, and I've forgotten
the money. I have to pay the taxi...

964
01:17:10,125 --> 01:17:14,167
I'm on my way.
Be right back.

965
01:17:34,000 --> 01:17:36,042
She is in the toilet.

966
01:17:43,667 --> 01:17:46,333
But..., but what has happened?

967
01:17:48,667 --> 01:17:51,333
We've had a big fight.

968
01:17:51,583 --> 01:17:55,292
Finally, he ripped my clothes off
and he threw me to the street half naked.

969
01:17:56,083 --> 01:18:01,750
Give the driver a tip, he has lended me his
jacket. If it wasn't for him...

970
01:18:02,000 --> 01:18:05,625
Son of a bitch! Right now we're
going to tell the police!

971
01:18:05,958 --> 01:18:11,125
No, Mateo!
Take me far away from here, please.

972
01:18:11,375 --> 01:18:15,083
Yes, yes, yes, of course. As you wish.

973
01:18:25,542 --> 01:18:36,958
("Werewolf" by Cat Power)

974
01:18:50,333 --> 01:18:53,333
Give me the camera.

975
01:19:35,750 --> 01:19:37,792
What are you writing?

976
01:19:39,000 --> 01:19:46,042
"El secreto de la Playa del Golfo" (The secret of the Gulf Beach).
When I took the picture I hadn't seen the couple kissing.

977
01:19:46,292 --> 01:19:48,417
And what is their secret?

978
01:19:48,583 --> 01:19:52,792
I don't know, I need to write it to figure out.

979
01:19:55,958 --> 01:19:58,833
That couple is us...

980
01:20:08,792 --> 01:20:13,625
(Off TV) "What is it?
It looks like a leg.

981
01:20:15,500 --> 01:20:22,917
(Off TV) It's an arm!
And the wto legs!"

982
01:20:53,458 --> 01:21:06,875
(beeps)

983
01:21:09,625 --> 01:21:12,042
(Off Harry) "Without noticing,
a month had already passed.

984
01:21:12,250 --> 01:21:17,250
I knew that, sooner or later,
we would have to go back, but we were postponing it.

985
01:21:17,417 --> 01:21:22,042
I was only worried about mum and you. I hadn't even
said goodbye to you,

986
01:21:22,292 --> 01:21:25,792
and you were with your allergies
when we left"

987
01:21:26,042 --> 01:21:30,792
(In english) Ok. The man with the bleach is
here. Do we need bleach? No? Ok. Over.

988
01:21:31,042 --> 01:21:39,250
Hi, sorry to interrupt... I just wanted to ask if you
have any possiblilities for work with you here.

989
01:21:40,125 --> 01:21:45,083
Well, we could use the help, especially now that
the high season is about to start.

990
01:21:46,375 --> 01:21:48,625
Have you got any experience?

991
01:21:48,875 --> 01:21:53,500
Yes, I have worked as a secretary in Madrid.
I am quite bilingual.

992
01:21:54,167 --> 01:21:57,375
She could start working here in the
afternoons... and then we could see.

993
01:21:58,458 --> 01:22:00,083
Wonderful!

994
01:22:00,833 --> 01:22:06,833
Excuse me, excuse me. We were just saying
that the girl in the ad looks exactly like you.

995
01:22:13,542 --> 01:22:16,417
No. It's not me.

996
01:22:23,875 --> 01:22:26,208
I was wondering how long it would take to appear!

997
01:22:26,458 --> 01:22:28,500
But they can't do the premiere so soon, can they?

998
01:22:28,750 --> 01:22:32,042
No, I did it to annoy us, it's a trap
for you to come back.

999
01:22:32,292 --> 01:22:34,875
The advertisment only needs a label that
reads "Wanted"

1000
01:22:35,125 --> 01:22:36,250
So what are we going to do?

1001
01:22:36,417 --> 01:22:39,458
Nothing. Fuck him.

1002
01:23:27,833 --> 01:23:29,542
What?

1003
01:23:31,042 --> 01:23:34,458
The only intelligent thing we've done
is not to go to the premiere...

1004
01:23:35,750 --> 01:23:38,417
Bastards!

1005
01:23:50,833 --> 01:23:57,667
(Off Harry) "Judit, it is I.
I need to talk urgently to you.

1006
01:23:57,917 --> 01:24:04,875
Call me, please!
This is my number... 845132

1007
01:24:05,000 --> 01:24:06,083
28...

1008
01:24:06,333 --> 01:24:14,625
Sorry... 28845132. Ah, and ask for Harry
Caine, I've given that name here.

1009
01:24:15,708 --> 01:24:21,917
Are you there?
I await your call!"

1010
01:24:22,667 --> 01:24:24,208
And mum didn't answer?

1011
01:24:24,375 --> 01:24:25,542
No.

1012
01:24:25,667 --> 01:24:26,958
Why?

1013
01:24:28,750 --> 01:24:32,000
Because she was upset, I guess.

1014
01:24:32,792 --> 01:24:37,333
But even if she was really angry, she
should have told you what was happening.

1015
01:24:37,583 --> 01:24:42,625
Yeah, the matter is that she didn't, and
we've never spoken about it.

1016
01:24:44,667 --> 01:24:46,375
And weren't you curious?

1017
01:24:46,542 --> 01:24:49,208
Me? I was dying f curiosity!

1018
01:24:49,458 --> 01:24:55,542
For two days I had been calling your mother and
Luis, the mounter, but nobody answered.

1019
01:24:56,333 --> 01:25:01,583
So I decided to go back to Madrid and see with
my own eyes what was happening.

1020
01:25:06,208 --> 01:25:09,292
It's the first time we split.

1021
01:25:09,542 --> 01:25:12,958
Anyway, I'll be back on the weekend.

1022
01:25:13,708 --> 01:25:16,917
But if you are going to stay here
worried, come with me.

1023
01:25:17,167 --> 01:25:22,958
No, I'm better off here.
Madrid scares me.

1024
01:25:50,083 --> 01:25:54,917
(Sinister metallic screeches)

1025
01:26:24,958 --> 01:26:30,333
( )

1026
01:26:34,458 --> 01:26:37,958
(Off Harry) "Magdalena's death didn't
surprise us hugging each other,

1027
01:26:38,208 --> 01:26:43,042
as we'd dreamed,
but in separate seats.

1028
01:26:43,500 --> 01:26:47,417
I was even surprised, leaving me alive."

1029
01:26:48,417 --> 01:26:53,250
Mateo...
Mateo, tell me something.

1030
01:26:54,875 --> 01:26:57,542
Mateo is dead, Judit.

1031
01:26:58,833 --> 01:27:00,875
Don't say that...

1032
01:27:01,125 --> 01:27:07,333
We call him with his name, but he refuses to
answer. Insists that Mateo is dead.

1033
01:27:08,625 --> 01:27:12,000
The pictures are the basis of his work.

1034
01:27:12,667 --> 01:27:21,708
Living in darkness, I guess was like death for him.
Is there any possibility that he sees again?

1035
01:27:21,958 --> 01:27:28,083
None. His is what we call cortical blindness,
and cannot be cured.

1036
01:27:28,417 --> 01:27:30,083
(Strong wind)

1037
01:27:30,625 --> 01:27:34,083
That is, very good, very good...

1038
01:27:37,167 --> 01:27:40,333
There are some stairs on the right side.

1039
01:27:42,250 --> 01:27:45,750
But it's not here, we have to go a
bit further.

1040
01:27:48,000 --> 01:27:50,792
Come on, I'll guide you
until we get to the border

1041
01:27:51,167 --> 01:27:59,833
Come on, that is... very good...
We're almost there.

1042
01:28:02,458 --> 01:28:05,250
Now there are some steps until we get to the car

1043
01:28:05,500 --> 01:28:08,375
and we're going to walk them slowly
because they are very high.

1044
01:28:08,625 --> 01:28:13,875
They are 25cm , I measured them before.
Wait, i'll leave you the bag.

1045
01:28:15,292 --> 01:28:21,083
Come on, let's go...

1046
01:28:22,667 --> 01:28:27,208
The first one is the hardest
but I'll hold you.

1047
01:28:31,208 --> 01:28:37,625
That is, slide your feet.
You're there. Let's go.

1048
01:28:41,417 --> 01:28:43,250
Very good...

1049
01:28:43,500 --> 01:28:46,792
Come on, now the second.
That's it...

1050
01:28:51,125 --> 01:28:57,000
A bit more.
There, that's it. No more steps.

1051
01:28:57,250 --> 01:29:00,583
Did you go to see Lena's mother in town?

1052
01:29:00,917 --> 01:29:02,625
Yes.

1053
01:29:02,875 --> 01:29:04,833
What did she say?

1054
01:29:07,167 --> 01:29:12,958
She was very pleased with Ernesto
for having taken care of everything.

1055
01:29:15,500 --> 01:29:16,917
Is he there?

1056
01:29:17,083 --> 01:29:21,375
Yes. She was buried with his father.

1057
01:29:21,625 --> 01:29:24,542
Did you see the tomb?

1058
01:29:24,750 --> 01:29:26,625
Yes.

1059
01:29:28,000 --> 01:29:30,708
How was it?

1060
01:29:31,833 --> 01:29:37,000
Simple.
The mother told me that they didn't want luxuries.

1061
01:29:46,417 --> 01:29:48,667
Look, mum, the sea!

1062
01:29:50,375 --> 01:29:52,833
We're in "Famara".

1063
01:29:53,083 --> 01:29:55,458
Please, stop!
I'm getting off here.

1064
01:29:55,708 --> 01:29:58,667
No, wait a second.
How are you going to get off here?

1065
01:29:59,250 --> 01:30:04,708
You go to the reception and do whatever
you have to do. I'll wait for you in the beach.

1066
01:30:04,958 --> 01:30:06,583
I want to get off here, too!

1067
01:30:06,833 --> 01:30:08,667
But how are you going to get off with this strong wind?

1068
01:30:08,917 --> 01:30:10,208
I'm not bothered by the wind.

1069
01:30:10,333 --> 01:30:12,625
Shut up, Diego, shut up!

1070
01:30:15,083 --> 01:30:17,333
Stop the car, please.

1071
01:30:30,375 --> 01:30:37,000
Mum, please. Let me stay, it's the first time
I've seen the sea, please...

1072
01:30:37,250 --> 01:30:39,708
Well, well..., all right. But be careful.

1073
01:30:40,458 --> 01:30:41,792
And don't get too close to the sea.

1074
01:30:41,917 --> 01:30:53,667
Give him your hand and don't let go, please.
Be careful with the wind, too. Oh, my god! That's it.

1075
01:30:56,708 --> 01:31:00,083
Careful, there's a step!

1076
01:31:10,125 --> 01:31:12,375
Please, let's go.

1077
01:31:21,375 --> 01:31:24,250
Wait here, please.

1078
01:31:35,958 --> 01:31:38,292
Good morning...
(In english) Good morning.

1079
01:31:38,542 --> 01:31:39,750
Good morning.
Good morning.

1080
01:31:39,875 --> 01:31:42,583
I am here to pay the Mateo Blanco's bill, please.

1081
01:31:42,750 --> 01:31:43,875
Who?

1082
01:31:44,083 --> 01:31:45,500
Mateo Blanco.

1083
01:31:45,750 --> 01:31:48,917
We dont have anyone here registered
by that name, right?

1084
01:31:49,167 --> 01:31:51,958
Its the man who had the accident.

1085
01:31:53,458 --> 01:31:55,792
You mean Harry Caine?

1086
01:31:56,792 --> 01:31:59,250
Yes... of course...

1087
01:33:18,875 --> 01:33:25,792
(Barking and wind)

1088
01:33:41,042 --> 01:33:44,750
(Shouts) Harry! Harry Caine!

1089
01:33:47,417 --> 01:33:50,917
We're here, Judit!

1090
01:34:00,833 --> 01:34:03,708
We have to go, Harry.

1091
01:34:03,958 --> 01:34:09,542
Let's go, Dieguito.
Dieguito, give me your hand.

1092
01:34:10,958 --> 01:34:13,333
Can't we stay here for a while longer?

1093
01:34:13,500 --> 01:34:17,583
No, you've had enough wind for today.

1094
01:34:22,708 --> 01:34:25,083
(whispers) I'm here... Harry.

1095
01:34:25,292 --> 01:34:28,500
Careful, don't trip over.

1096
01:34:42,833 --> 01:34:45,750
Do you remember "Famara", Diego?

1097
01:34:46,083 --> 01:34:47,250
Perfectly.

1098
01:34:47,417 --> 01:34:53,083
It was the first time I saw the sea. I remember
the kytes and a dog barking.

1099
01:34:55,625 --> 01:34:59,542
I remember that dog barking as well...

1100
01:35:07,708 --> 01:35:09,542
What are you doing?

1101
01:35:09,792 --> 01:35:13,292
I'm trying to reconstruct your pictures...

1102
01:35:30,750 --> 01:35:33,125
I have almost one complete...

1103
01:35:36,667 --> 01:35:38,708
What do you want to do to cheer you up a bit?

1104
01:35:38,917 --> 01:35:40,958
I'd like to hear Jeanne Moreau's voice.

1105
01:35:41,125 --> 01:35:42,792
Well I don't have the phone.

1106
01:35:42,917 --> 01:35:45,917
Search "Ascensor para el cadalso" by Louis Malle.

1107
01:35:46,167 --> 01:35:50,500
Ok.Fritz Lang, Jules Dassin,
Nicholas Ray...

1108
01:35:50,958 --> 01:35:53,417
Search on the top.

1109
01:35:55,208 --> 01:35:58,500
"Fanny and Alexander", "Fellini Eight and a half",
"Obsession"...

1110
01:35:59,083 --> 01:36:03,208
"Ascensor para el cadalso", I've got it here.
I haven't seen it.

1111
01:36:03,458 --> 01:36:05,375
I hope you like it.

1112
01:36:09,708 --> 01:36:11,833
(TV)
Are you crazy? How am I going to throw it away?

1113
01:36:12,083 --> 01:36:14,208
What I have to do is to make the police find it
in my house.

1114
01:36:14,375 --> 01:36:16,917
Leave that! That is "Chicas y maletas"!

1115
01:36:17,333 --> 01:36:19,667
But I don't understand...

1116
01:36:20,042 --> 01:36:22,208
Well that's pretty clear.

1117
01:36:22,667 --> 01:36:28,125
If the police finds in my place 15 kilos of
uncut coke, I could get arrested.

1118
01:36:29,250 --> 01:36:35,125
Yes, but I don't understand how that suitcase
has appeared in your home, like that...

1119
01:36:36,208 --> 01:36:38,333
Sounds strange, doesn't it?

1120
01:36:42,042 --> 01:36:47,500
As I was telling you..., after breaking appart with
my husband I went to the street,

1121
01:36:48,292 --> 01:36:51,375
And I saw that guy who was glncing at me,
very good looking.

1122
01:36:51,625 --> 01:36:57,083
What an ass, and his feet...
I brought home and I fucked him several times.

1123
01:36:57,333 --> 01:36:58,875
They are totally out of tune...

1124
01:36:59,125 --> 01:37:02,708
In bed, a virtuous.

1125
01:37:03,167 --> 01:37:05,208
Look at my goosebumps...

1126
01:37:05,333 --> 01:37:10,375
How could I take those shots as good?
They are both horrible!

1127
01:37:12,208 --> 01:37:14,375
What do you want to to today?

1128
01:37:14,833 --> 01:37:19,167
I have to go home. My mother has left a message
saying that she's back today,

1129
01:37:19,417 --> 01:37:22,083
ready to celebrate your birthday.

1130
01:37:22,750 --> 01:37:25,000
Is it my birthday?

1131
01:37:25,167 --> 01:37:26,750
So she says.

1132
01:37:26,917 --> 01:37:29,042
If Judit says so...

1133
01:37:29,292 --> 01:37:30,708
Congratulations, man!

1134
01:37:30,958 --> 01:37:33,750
So, I will have to invite you for supper.

1135
01:37:38,583 --> 01:37:40,417
Is there anybody at home?

1136
01:37:42,833 --> 01:37:44,250
Yes.

1137
01:37:44,625 --> 01:37:48,542
Oh, my son, I wanted to see you so much!

1138
01:37:51,583 --> 01:37:54,833
What happens? Is it very noticeable?

1139
01:37:55,000 --> 01:37:56,250
Well, yes.

1140
01:37:56,417 --> 01:37:59,792
I haven't even had time to wipe
my ass, today.

1141
01:38:00,042 --> 01:38:03,750
Well, don't look at me like that...
I thought you had already gotten used to.

1142
01:38:04,000 --> 01:38:05,833
Yes, sorry...

1143
01:38:06,083 --> 01:38:11,875
You are beautiful, very beautiful. Are you ok?
You had me very worried.

1144
01:38:12,125 --> 01:38:15,625
I'm fine.
Mateo has taken care of me day and night...

1145
01:38:15,875 --> 01:38:19,875
Mateo?
Isn't your name Harry anymore?

1146
01:38:20,125 --> 01:38:21,667
Yes...

1147
01:38:23,875 --> 01:38:27,292
We have to buy him a birthday
present.

1148
01:38:28,875 --> 01:38:31,333
Well..., what have you been doing all this time?

1149
01:38:31,708 --> 01:38:35,292
Nothing... watch movies...
and talk.

1150
01:38:36,500 --> 01:38:38,042
Talk?

1151
01:38:38,167 --> 01:38:39,375
Yes.

1152
01:38:39,542 --> 01:38:41,250
(Dry) What about?

1153
01:38:41,375 --> 01:38:43,375
My God, mum!

1154
01:38:49,208 --> 01:38:51,250
Well..., what did you have?

1155
01:38:51,500 --> 01:38:56,458
I don't know if I should believe the gastroenteritis...
you used it already as an excuse in a script...

1156
01:38:56,708 --> 01:39:00,833
I had... an accident.
But I'd rather not talk about it now.

1157
01:39:01,083 --> 01:39:05,083
An accident?
What sort of accident?

1158
01:39:05,875 --> 01:39:07,167
It's hard to explain.

1159
01:39:07,333 --> 01:39:09,375
Try it! I'm not THAT stupid!

1160
01:39:09,625 --> 01:39:12,708
We'll leave it for another
time, ok? I'm fine now.

1161
01:39:14,083 --> 01:39:17,292
Well, I'm going to buy some DVDs to Mateo.

1162
01:39:27,625 --> 01:39:29,125
We're closing.

1163
01:39:29,375 --> 01:39:31,000
I know, this is the last one.

1164
01:39:31,167 --> 01:39:32,708
Thanks.

1165
01:39:45,333 --> 01:39:47,292
Thank you.

1166
01:39:52,750 --> 01:39:56,042
I don't know what have you been
talking all these days...

1167
01:39:57,833 --> 01:40:01,542
But I know what I haven't told you all
these years.

1168
01:40:01,917 --> 01:40:04,042
I've never asked you...

1169
01:40:04,292 --> 01:40:07,375
But you might have wondered it
yourself thousands of times.

1170
01:40:07,833 --> 01:40:11,042
This is my bithday present, Mateo.

1171
01:40:11,917 --> 01:40:14,458
The present is also for you, Diego.

1172
01:40:19,417 --> 01:40:23,625
After your vanishing, Ernesto Sr. only
wanted vengeance...

1173
01:40:23,875 --> 01:40:25,000
Drop it, Judit.

1174
01:40:25,125 --> 01:40:26,208
No.

1175
01:40:26,333 --> 01:40:27,542
You've had a bad day today.

1176
01:40:27,667 --> 01:40:30,917
That's why, I'd like to finish it a bit better.

1177
01:40:33,167 --> 01:40:38,125
Ernesto had a delusional plan to take vengeance
on you, but to perform it

1178
01:40:38,792 --> 01:40:43,750
he had to bribe us, at least,
Luis, the mounter, and me.

1179
01:40:44,917 --> 01:40:53,000
Despite the delusional bit, there was no problem,
we sold ourselves without any resistance. Luis and I.

1180
01:40:54,083 --> 01:40:59,042
With me, well, he gave me an alibi,

1181
01:40:59,417 --> 01:41:01,875
he proposed me to go a month and
a half to the U.S.,

1182
01:41:02,125 --> 01:41:06,875
to the Clínica Mayo, so Dieguito
could cure the aspergilosis (fungal disease),

1183
01:41:07,125 --> 01:41:13,208
that way, I wouldn't be there whist
he... ruined your movie.

1184
01:41:13,792 --> 01:41:19,583
Because that was his plan,
to reduce your movie to dust.

1185
01:41:24,917 --> 01:41:31,542
I prefered to stay in Madrid and cure Diego
here. I wanted to witness everything.

1186
01:41:31,792 --> 01:41:37,292
If I was going to betray you, I wanted
to pay the price for it.

1187
01:41:39,833 --> 01:41:45,417
It was a torture to see how Ernesto
was choosing the worst takes of each shot

1188
01:41:45,750 --> 01:41:50,708
and Luis was mounting them, transforming
your movie in a monster.

1189
01:41:51,792 --> 01:41:56,125
The only way to resist all of that
was to suffer more.

1190
01:41:56,792 --> 01:42:03,208
I sold myself to Ernesto for pain and jealousy!
I didn't accept it, and I didn't forgave you

1191
01:42:03,458 --> 01:42:07,500
for abandoning "Cinearte" with
Lena without a single word.

1192
01:42:07,958 --> 01:42:16,250
With my treason, I took vengeance upon you,
her, and myself.... The only innocent was Diego.

1193
01:42:17,750 --> 01:42:23,333
Sorry, son, for all the bitterness
I've given you all this years.

1194
01:42:24,417 --> 01:42:27,583
Nobody deserves to grow like that...

1195
01:42:44,000 --> 01:42:47,083
May I have another G&T, please?

1196
01:42:55,542 --> 01:42:58,333
Don't look at me like that.

1197
01:43:08,292 --> 01:43:10,208
Thank you.

1198
01:43:22,417 --> 01:43:25,625
Please, Judit, don't continue.
There is no need.

1199
01:43:25,875 --> 01:43:30,208
Yes. Now that your name is Mateo again
I have no excuse anymore.

1200
01:43:30,458 --> 01:43:32,708
You have told us everything.

1201
01:43:33,458 --> 01:43:36,458
No... not everything.

1202
01:43:45,333 --> 01:43:49,042
Nobody knew where you were.
We had no idea.

1203
01:43:49,917 --> 01:43:55,500
Ernesto prepared everything, the premiere,
all that, so you reacted.

1204
01:43:55,875 --> 01:44:00,292
His vengeance had no meaning
if neither of you took notice.

1205
01:44:01,292 --> 01:44:04,375
Ernesto was asking me constantly
about your whereabouts,

1206
01:44:04,708 --> 01:44:08,208
but I knew nothing, either,
which was true.

1207
01:44:08,458 --> 01:44:12,583
I didn't want to call you for that,
to avoid making your life more difficult.

1208
01:44:13,458 --> 01:44:17,375
Ernesto hired some detectives
to find you.

1209
01:44:18,167 --> 01:44:26,125
But, before they found you,
you phoned me, two days after the premiere.

1210
01:44:28,167 --> 01:44:34,875
I was too shocked to answer your call.

1211
01:44:35,125 --> 01:44:37,500
I still am.

1212
01:44:39,208 --> 01:44:48,750
When ernesto asked about you again,
I don't know why, I gave the phone to "Famara".

1213
01:44:52,833 --> 01:44:57,083
Ernesto sent his son to
find you to Lanzarote.

1214
01:45:04,500 --> 01:45:10,208
It was Ernesto Jr the one who found you
after the accident and phoned the hospital...

1215
01:45:10,458 --> 01:45:12,375
Did he had anything to do with the accident?

1216
01:45:12,625 --> 01:45:18,208
No! But I can't stop thinking that should I
hadn't given the phone number to his father...

1217
01:45:18,875 --> 01:45:22,375
maybe nothing would have happened...

1218
01:45:24,292 --> 01:45:26,542
Why do you think that?

1219
01:45:28,583 --> 01:45:32,583
I don't know... bad conscience, I guess.

1220
01:45:32,833 --> 01:45:37,375
Well it's enough, then! 14 years of
bad conscience are enough!

1221
01:46:04,833 --> 01:46:06,750
Wait, I'll help you.

1222
01:46:07,542 --> 01:46:11,125
No, thanks.
Good night.

1223
01:46:17,625 --> 01:46:21,458
Call if you need anything!

1224
01:46:39,625 --> 01:46:43,750
(mobile phone)

1225
01:46:46,083 --> 01:46:50,000
(Off answering machine)
"Diego. Not answering. Leave your message"

1226
01:46:50,458 --> 01:46:53,000
Hi Diego, is Mateo...

1227
01:46:55,458 --> 01:47:02,375
I'm sorry about calling you so early. Tell your
mother to call me as soon as she can. Thanks.

1228
01:47:34,083 --> 01:47:35,958
Harry, so early. How comes?

1229
01:47:36,125 --> 01:47:37,333
I couldn't sleep.

1230
01:47:37,458 --> 01:47:39,167
Oh... Coffee and toast?

1231
01:47:39,500 --> 01:47:43,208
Yes, but before,
Would you mind calling me at this number?

1232
01:47:45,542 --> 01:47:47,292
Ray X?

1233
01:47:54,083 --> 01:47:55,500
Here...

1234
01:47:55,667 --> 01:47:56,875
Thanks.

1235
01:47:57,042 --> 01:47:59,000
I'll bring you the coffee.

1236
01:47:59,250 --> 01:48:00,500
Ernesto?

1237
01:48:00,667 --> 01:48:01,833
(Off) Who is this?

1238
01:48:01,958 --> 01:48:05,000
I'm sorry to bother you,
I'm Mateo Blanco.

1239
01:48:20,542 --> 01:48:22,792
What nonsense!

1240
01:48:23,042 --> 01:48:25,000
One has to start the day with the good foot.

1241
01:48:28,167 --> 01:48:29,667
How are you feeling?

1242
01:48:30,042 --> 01:48:36,125
A bit hangover, but fine. I think that
yesterday's catharsis, in the end, felt great.

1243
01:48:37,125 --> 01:48:38,875
Come on, let me help you.

1244
01:48:39,083 --> 01:48:42,542
No, sit down, sit down...

1245
01:48:44,625 --> 01:48:48,625
Diego, I only needed to tell you
something else.

1246
01:48:48,875 --> 01:48:51,458
You'll tell me later.
Let's have breakfast now.

1247
01:48:51,708 --> 01:48:55,000
If I don't tell you now, maybe
I won't ever tell you...

1248
01:48:56,750 --> 01:49:01,750
At the end of the 80's, Mateo and I
had an affaire.

1249
01:49:03,042 --> 01:49:06,875
But I imagined that already, even
before yesterday's catharsis.

1250
01:49:07,125 --> 01:49:08,542
Did you?

1251
01:49:08,708 --> 01:49:09,792
Mum, it's obvious!

1252
01:49:10,042 --> 01:49:11,958
The same curtains in his bedroom
than in yours,

1253
01:49:12,208 --> 01:49:15,083
memorabilia from Mexico and the Caribbean
in both homes, the crosses...

1254
01:49:15,958 --> 01:49:20,625
Of course...
There's something else that I don't think you know.

1255
01:49:22,750 --> 01:49:24,792
Mateo is your father.

1256
01:49:25,667 --> 01:49:27,708
Mateo, my dad?

1257
01:49:27,958 --> 01:49:29,583
Yes.

1258
01:49:30,542 --> 01:49:36,875
And your lover who went, my supposed
biological father, you made it up?

1259
01:49:37,125 --> 01:49:42,708
No... I can't hide things,
but I never make anything up. I can't invent.

1260
01:49:43,250 --> 01:49:51,333
The lover existed. We had an adventure.
He was gay, and the adventure lasted little.

1261
01:49:53,792 --> 01:49:54,875
Does Mateo know?

1262
01:49:55,250 --> 01:50:01,250
No. Are you crazy! In that time, he
asked me, and I, of course, negated it.

1263
01:50:01,708 --> 01:50:06,042
I didn't press him, I didn't want our relationship
to change because of that.

1264
01:50:06,292 --> 01:50:09,542
In the end, I didn't ask him either
if he wanted to be your dad.

1265
01:50:10,125 --> 01:50:12,792
Ha! Bastard!
So Mateo is my father...

1266
01:50:15,250 --> 01:50:18,125
By the way, he phoned early this
morning.

1267
01:50:18,375 --> 01:50:20,958
Mateo? What did he want?

1268
01:50:21,208 --> 01:50:22,500
He wanted you to call him as soon as you could.

1269
01:50:22,667 --> 01:50:24,167
Why didn't you wake me up?

1270
01:50:24,417 --> 01:50:27,708
Because after yesterday you needed some
sleep, and he didn't say it was urgent.

1271
01:50:27,958 --> 01:50:29,500
You can call him now.

1272
01:50:29,667 --> 01:50:31,875
Come on, give me the phone.

1273
01:50:36,375 --> 01:50:37,667
Hello?

1274
01:50:37,792 --> 01:50:42,292
Hi. Diego told me to call you.
Are you OK? Do you need anything?

1275
01:50:42,542 --> 01:50:46,042
I'm not fine, Judit.
And yes, I need something...

1276
01:50:46,583 --> 01:50:50,917
The 40.000 metres of negative that we recorded
on my last movie to mount it.

1277
01:50:52,333 --> 01:50:57,917
I'm at Ernesto Jr's home and I have just been
told that the material was destroyed in 1994.

1278
01:50:59,083 --> 01:51:03,542
I imagined something like that, but I didn't
think they would do it so soon.

1279
01:51:03,667 --> 01:51:05,000
What are you doing at Ernesto's?

1280
01:51:05,250 --> 01:51:09,875
I think I'm going to blackmail him.
We need money and he has plenty.

1281
01:51:10,125 --> 01:51:14,250
I don't want Diego to go back to that
damned bar, I want to pay him a salary.

1282
01:51:17,000 --> 01:51:18,625
Mateo, don't be crazy!

1283
01:51:18,875 --> 01:51:22,583
I can't figure out anyone else to blame
for Magdalena's death.

1284
01:51:22,833 --> 01:51:27,167
My god!
Wait, I have something to tell you!

1285
01:51:27,542 --> 01:51:30,083
Leave it, you said enough yesterday.

1286
01:51:30,333 --> 01:51:34,583
Listen, Mateo! I was the production
director of the movie,

1287
01:51:34,833 --> 01:51:37,792
the only person who had access to
the lab and the material.

1288
01:51:39,292 --> 01:51:43,833
After Ernesto gave the order for it to be destroyed,
I intercepted it and kept it.

1289
01:51:44,083 --> 01:51:45,917
I have everything at home.

1290
01:51:46,083 --> 01:51:48,583
You're lying.

1291
01:51:48,750 --> 01:51:52,292
I didn't tell you yesterday because I didn't know
that you wanted to mount it again.

1292
01:51:52,542 --> 01:51:58,750
I kept it. All the double shots,
the negative, the sound tracks, everything!

1293
01:51:59,000 --> 01:52:01,000
You can have everything whenever you want!
That changes everything.

1294
01:52:01,167 --> 01:52:02,292
That changes everything.

1295
01:52:02,417 --> 01:52:07,583
Get out of there, Mateo, and leave Ernesto alone.
He has nothing to do with this.

1296
01:52:07,833 --> 01:52:13,958
He still has to tell me what he was doing in
Lanzarote. Goodbye, Judit. I'll call you later.

1297
01:52:21,167 --> 01:52:26,750
Ernesto and his camera...
You remind me of a Peeping Tom.

1298
01:52:27,000 --> 01:52:30,917
Yes, but I never wanted to kill you.

1299
01:52:31,167 --> 01:52:33,958
I'm not so sure about that.

1300
01:52:34,917 --> 01:52:37,792
I have here a copy of the "making of"
that proves it.

1301
01:52:39,625 --> 01:52:41,667
Why do I want that?
I can't watch it!

1302
01:52:41,917 --> 01:52:45,833
Someone you trust should watch it and
tell you. Sorry...

1303
01:52:46,583 --> 01:52:49,583
With this pictures the documentary about
Mateo Blanco ends,

1304
01:52:49,833 --> 01:52:52,167
also called Harry Caine...

1305
01:53:37,458 --> 01:53:40,042
What do you think of the documentary,
how should I name it, Ernesto?

1306
01:53:42,167 --> 01:53:44,417
Very interesting.

1307
01:53:45,375 --> 01:53:47,208
What do you see now?

1308
01:53:48,500 --> 01:53:51,500
The last night,
when you're on your way back from the restaurant.

1309
01:53:51,750 --> 01:53:55,458
How was he able to film us?
The night was very dark...

1310
01:53:56,833 --> 01:54:00,958
His car's lights and the lighting from the
statue were enough

1311
01:54:01,208 --> 01:54:07,542
to see what happened. Anyway, he has touched digitally
the picture.

1312
01:54:08,000 --> 01:54:11,500
Mateo, Ernesto not only did not provoke
the accident,

1313
01:54:11,833 --> 01:54:14,500
but he was also the first person who
came to help you.

1314
01:54:14,750 --> 01:54:17,542
How was he able to film and drive at the same time?

1315
01:54:17,750 --> 01:54:19,750
I don't know...

1316
01:54:19,958 --> 01:54:25,875
Is there anything else that I need to know?
What are you seeing now?

1317
01:54:27,167 --> 01:54:32,958
You are waiting in the roundabout for a car to go through
the left. Lena and you kiss...

1318
01:54:33,208 --> 01:54:35,958
A kiss? I don't remember...

1319
01:54:36,750 --> 01:54:41,500
It's a normal kiss, one of those that couples
give by inertia.

1320
01:54:42,667 --> 01:54:45,125
The last kiss...

1321
01:54:45,500 --> 01:54:51,500
Yes... Lena didn't die in your arms, as
you two had dreamed,

1322
01:54:52,458 --> 01:54:59,000
but the last feeling she had in this
world, was the flavour of your mouth...

1323
01:55:07,250 --> 01:55:09,042
Is it there?

1324
01:55:09,208 --> 01:55:11,583
Yes.

1325
01:55:13,500 --> 01:55:18,167
Play it frame by frame, so it
lasts longer...

1326
01:55:57,375 --> 01:56:03,583
(Off Harry) 14 years after the filming,
I was finally able to mount "Girls and luggage".

1327
01:56:13,292 --> 01:56:18,167
On my way!
Ah, it's you.

1328
01:56:18,417 --> 01:56:19,792
I've left thousands of notes!

1329
01:56:19,958 --> 01:56:21,625
Yes, a thousand yours, and none from Ivan.

1330
01:56:21,958 --> 01:56:23,208
And that case!

1331
01:56:23,375 --> 01:56:25,333
It's Ivan's. I'm borowing it.

1332
01:56:25,583 --> 01:56:26,833
And the crutches?

1333
01:56:27,000 --> 01:56:29,917
His ex wife, the bitch. She pushed me down the stairs.

1334
01:56:30,167 --> 01:56:32,625
Wow, what a pair of us!
I've splitted also with my husband.

1335
01:56:32,875 --> 01:56:36,708
Oh, I'm sorry. Listen, I was doing coffee,
would you mind to serve it?

1336
01:56:36,958 --> 01:56:38,208
No.

1337
01:56:38,333 --> 01:56:41,708
I've spent the whole night searching for Ivan,
and I've had a pic session afterwards

1338
01:56:41,917 --> 01:56:43,417
and I've had no sleep yet.

1339
01:56:43,542 --> 01:56:45,042
Neither have I!

1340
01:56:45,167 --> 01:56:46,583
Hey, when did you split?

1341
01:56:46,833 --> 01:56:48,958
Four days ago. Sugar?

1342
01:56:49,083 --> 01:56:50,375
No.

1343
01:56:50,542 --> 01:56:52,750
I foresaw it.
Thing is that, after splitting,

1344
01:56:53,000 --> 01:56:55,333
I go out to the street and I discover
that guy looking at me.

1345
01:56:55,792 --> 01:56:58,000
Oh, gazpacho! I'm going to serve myself a glass.

1346
01:56:58,167 --> 01:56:59,333
(Shouts) No!

1347
01:56:59,500 --> 01:57:01,917
I've put a whole box of sleeping pills in there.

1348
01:57:02,167 --> 01:57:03,667
Why so?

1349
01:57:03,917 --> 01:57:06,917
Just in case Ivan came, he likes
gazpacho a lot.

1350
01:57:07,167 --> 01:57:08,250
My dear, Pina!

1351
01:57:08,833 --> 01:57:11,375
That's nothing! Since he wasn't calling,
I've ripped the phone off the wall.

1352
01:57:11,625 --> 01:57:13,375
I've stumbled upon it, and
I haven't asked anything

1353
01:57:13,625 --> 01:57:15,958
because I didn't want to ask too much...

1354
01:57:16,417 --> 01:57:20,333
But... that bed?
It's smoking, isn't it?

1355
01:57:20,583 --> 01:57:25,958
The match fell, and started burning, and
I didn't want to put it off. Fire purifies.

1356
01:57:26,208 --> 01:57:27,750
Bring your coffee!

1357
01:57:31,625 --> 01:57:33,042
You were telling me something, Chon?

1358
01:57:34,250 --> 01:57:36,167
Ah, yes..., yes!

1359
01:57:41,375 --> 01:57:46,917
I was telling you...
I also have a case at home.

1360
01:57:47,167 --> 01:57:48,250
Your husband's?

1361
01:57:48,375 --> 01:57:49,625
No.

1362
01:57:49,875 --> 01:57:54,125
A case with 15 kilos of coke,
uncut..., delicious...

1363
01:57:54,375 --> 01:57:55,917
Are you now a drug dealer, Chon?

1364
01:57:56,042 --> 01:58:01,833
I'm still chancellor of Social Services.
The case appeared in my wardrobe, suddently.

1365
01:58:03,417 --> 01:58:06,208
I have to dispose of those
15 kilos as soon as possible.

1366
01:58:07,083 --> 01:58:09,417
With the time schedule we have in
politics, we take plenty of drugs.

1367
01:58:09,667 --> 01:58:12,958
Between the members of the party and in
the Council, I could deliver up to 2 kilos,

1368
01:58:13,125 --> 01:58:14,958
But what do I do with the rest?!

1369
01:58:15,083 --> 01:58:16,167
Throw it away!

1370
01:58:16,333 --> 01:58:17,542
Are you mad!
How am I going to throw it away?

1371
01:58:17,792 --> 01:58:20,458
What I need to do is avoid the
police finding it at home...

1372
01:58:20,833 --> 01:58:22,000
But, I don't know how...

1373
01:58:22,125 --> 01:58:23,500
Well it's very clear to me!

1374
01:58:23,625 --> 01:58:25,875
If the police catches me with 15 kilos of
uncut, delicious coke at home,

1375
01:58:26,042 --> 01:58:27,458
they could get me arrested.

1376
01:58:27,708 --> 01:58:31,708
Yeah, Chon, but I don't understand how that
case appeared in your wardrobe, like that, suddently!

1377
01:58:35,625 --> 01:58:38,083
As I was telling you...
After splitting with my husband,

1378
01:58:38,333 --> 01:58:42,750
I went outside, and I met a guy who
was staring at me. Good looking.

1379
01:58:43,333 --> 01:58:48,792
What an arse, feet... Well, I brought him
home and I fucked him several times.

1380
01:58:49,042 --> 01:58:52,542
You know that I'm very interested in sex,
as a social matter...

1381
01:58:53,833 --> 01:58:55,583
And how was he?

1382
01:58:55,750 --> 01:58:57,542
In ved? A virtuoso.

1383
01:58:57,792 --> 01:59:05,250
I've never seen anything like that!
Look at my goosebumps!

1384
01:59:05,708 --> 01:59:07,042
So what happened afterwards?

1385
01:59:07,292 --> 01:59:11,500
Nothing, after fucking he asked me if he
could stay some days in my place.

1386
01:59:11,750 --> 01:59:13,625
Do you have magdalenas?

1387
01:59:13,750 --> 01:59:15,250
Yes, there, up in the cabinet.

1388
01:59:15,833 --> 01:59:17,792
And I have a lovely flan.

1389
01:59:17,917 --> 01:59:19,500
I'll eat that afterwards!

1390
01:59:20,583 --> 01:59:23,167
So, he asked me if he could stay at home.

1391
01:59:23,417 --> 01:59:25,375
I said well, but I couldn't
promise anything.

1392
01:59:25,625 --> 01:59:27,875
I didn't want him to think that I was an easy woman.

1393
01:59:28,125 --> 01:59:31,625
Thing is, he appeared at home with a case
and installed himself there.

1394
01:59:32,708 --> 01:59:35,583
I was yesterday evening watching TV...

1395
01:59:36,250 --> 01:59:40,792
And I learned that the police has caught
him in an anti-drugs raid

1396
01:59:41,250 --> 01:59:44,833
and that he's one of the most wanted
drug dealers of the country!

1397
01:59:45,083 --> 01:59:46,833
No way!

1398
01:59:47,792 --> 01:59:56,208
With the tingling nose, I open the case and
I see that it's full of cocaine bags.

1399
01:59:59,583 --> 02:00:05,667
I took one... went out the street
and since then I've not gone back.

1400
02:00:06,458 --> 02:00:08,292
What a story, my God!

1401
02:00:08,542 --> 02:00:11,208
It was strange that he fucked so good!

1402
02:00:12,083 --> 02:00:16,208
For men who live in that sort of risky life,
every fuck is like the last one.

1403
02:00:16,458 --> 02:00:20,042
And, of course, there's no colour!
Look at my goosebumps!

1404
02:00:20,292 --> 02:00:24,208
I saw it before...
You have it so easy! And the case?

1405
02:00:24,375 --> 02:00:31,208
The case... well, I wanted to ask you...
if you don't mind me bringing it here.

1406
02:00:32,000 --> 02:00:33,083
Can you hear me?

1407
02:00:33,208 --> 02:00:34,292
(Off) Yes, I can hear you.

1408
02:00:34,417 --> 02:00:39,083
I'm going to bring it here. If it's found in
my place, it's  not because of what could happen to me,

1409
02:00:39,250 --> 02:00:41,083
which is not the ideal thing
for a Social chancellor,

1410
02:00:41,542 --> 02:00:44,958
but do you imagine the shock to the
Mayor and my party?

1411
02:00:45,208 --> 02:00:47,667
